1
00:00:58,977 --> 00:01:00,603
<i>Mutants...</i>

2
00:01:00,770 --> 00:01:03,731
<i>born with extraordinary abilities...</i>

3
00:01:04,649 --> 00:01:08,945
<i>and yet, still, they are children
stumbling in the dark...</i>

4
00:01:09,112 --> 00:01:10,780
<i>searching for guidance.</i>

5
00:01:12,407 --> 00:01:15,326
<i>A gift can often be a curse.</i>

6
00:01:16,494 --> 00:01:20,790
<i>Give someone wings,
and they may fly too close to the sun.</i>

7
00:01:22,750 --> 00:01:25,003
<i>Give them the power of prophecy...</i>

8
00:01:25,169 --> 00:01:27,505
<i>and they may live in fear of the future.</i>

9
00:01:28,172 --> 00:01:30,258
<i>Give them the greatest gifts of all...</i>

10
00:01:31,092 --> 00:01:33,678
<i>powers beyond imagination...</i>

11
00:01:34,429 --> 00:01:38,182
<i>and they may think they're meant
to rule the world.</i>

12
00:01:53,781 --> 00:01:56,784
En Sabah Nur.

13
00:01:56,951 --> 00:01:59,954
En Sabah Nur.

14
00:03:19,701 --> 00:03:23,162
Now you will rule for eternity, my lord.

15
00:03:37,593 --> 00:03:39,345
Sleep.

16
00:03:41,931 --> 00:03:45,268
Let the transference begin.

17
00:05:14,065 --> 00:05:16,067
Death to the false god.

18
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:37,755
Protect him!

19
00:08:20,292 --> 00:08:23,838
{\an8}As everyone knows, the existence
of mutants was first discovered...

20
00:08:23,921 --> 00:08:28,092
during the Paris Peace Accords,
after the Vietnam War in 1973.

21
00:08:28,467 --> 00:08:31,262
{\an8}Six days later, we all watched
as one of those mutants...

22
00:08:33,347 --> 00:08:35,516
Erik Lehnsherr, attacked the President...

23
00:08:35,683 --> 00:08:38,227
and the Cabinet on the lawn
of the White House.

24
00:08:38,394 --> 00:08:42,356
Their lives were saved
by a young mutant who stopped him.

25
00:08:42,523 --> 00:08:46,569
Now, Lehnsherr escaped and became
the world's most-wanted fugitive.

26
00:08:46,736 --> 00:08:48,336
And as for her, she disappeared as well.

27
00:08:48,487 --> 00:08:51,657
But she has become the symbol
of a new age...

28
00:08:51,824 --> 00:08:54,243
the face of a world
that will never be the same again.

29
00:08:54,410 --> 00:08:56,078
You winking at my girl?

30
00:08:57,204 --> 00:08:58,330
Your girl?

31
00:08:59,081 --> 00:09:01,459
I guess you do look old enough
to be her father.

32
00:09:02,626 --> 00:09:03,669
Excuse me, gentlemen...

33
00:09:03,836 --> 00:09:06,630
is there something you'd like
to share with the rest of the class?

34
00:09:06,797 --> 00:09:08,507
Can I please go to the bathroom?

35
00:09:08,674 --> 00:09:10,834
I think there's something
seriously wrong with my eyes.

36
00:09:11,177 --> 00:09:12,344
Fine, Scott.
And afterwards...

37
00:09:12,511 --> 00:09:15,073
why don't you stop by the principal's
office and explain to him...

38
00:09:15,097 --> 00:09:16,497
that you're disrupting class again?

39
00:09:17,850 --> 00:09:19,560
I trust you know the way.

40
00:09:19,727 --> 00:09:21,103
- Yeah, I do.
- Okay.

41
00:09:21,771 --> 00:09:23,898
No, hang on! Hang on!

42
00:09:27,693 --> 00:09:28,736
Hey!

43
00:09:28,903 --> 00:09:31,155
Now, I know most of you were, what?

44
00:09:31,322 --> 00:09:33,032
Around seven years old at that time?

45
00:09:43,542 --> 00:09:44,960
Summers!

46
00:09:46,295 --> 00:09:48,589
I know you're in here.

47
00:09:49,757 --> 00:09:51,050
What, are you crying?

48
00:09:52,009 --> 00:09:53,409
I haven't even kicked your ass yet.

49
00:09:55,930 --> 00:09:57,848
Summers! You want to eyeball my girl?

50
00:10:45,521 --> 00:10:46,480
Yeah!

51
00:10:46,564 --> 00:10:48,149
Ten fights waged.

52
00:10:48,232 --> 00:10:49,692
Ten fights won.

53
00:10:49,859 --> 00:10:51,569
The Winged Warrior.

54
00:10:52,111 --> 00:10:53,571
The Bird of Prey.

55
00:10:53,737 --> 00:10:54,989
The Angel of Death.

56
00:10:55,072 --> 00:10:56,574
ANGEL!

57
00:10:56,907 --> 00:10:57,992
Yeah!

58
00:11:03,247 --> 00:11:06,292
Let's hear it for the fat man!

59
00:11:06,834 --> 00:11:09,253
Our next challenger...

60
00:11:09,587 --> 00:11:10,921
comes straight...

61
00:11:11,255 --> 00:11:14,258
from the Munich Circus.

62
00:11:15,384 --> 00:11:16,260
Ladies and gentlemen,

63
00:11:17,094 --> 00:11:20,181
the only one that could
take on an Angel...

64
00:11:20,264 --> 00:11:21,599
is the Devil himself.

65
00:11:23,267 --> 00:11:24,852
I give you...

66
00:11:25,769 --> 00:11:27,188
the amazing...

67
00:11:27,855 --> 00:11:29,231
the fantastic...

68
00:11:30,107 --> 00:11:32,401
NIGHTCRAWLER!

69
00:11:52,129 --> 00:11:52,962
Caution

70
00:11:53,047 --> 00:11:54,506
High voltage!

71
00:11:54,757 --> 00:11:56,842
Sorry mutants!

72
00:12:11,982 --> 00:12:13,192
Hey.

73
00:12:13,275 --> 00:12:15,236
Did you get lost little mouse?

74
00:12:15,361 --> 00:12:16,737
The fight is over there.

75
00:12:19,823 --> 00:12:20,741
Fight!

76
00:12:20,908 --> 00:12:22,159
Or they'll kill us both!

77
00:12:25,246 --> 00:12:26,830
And it's about to get exciting.

78
00:12:27,790 --> 00:12:29,166
Ah, you mean this?

79
00:12:50,104 --> 00:12:51,939
Nightcrawler!

80
00:12:56,652 --> 00:12:59,029
Nightcrawler! Nightcrawler!

81
00:12:59,196 --> 00:13:00,030
I'm sorry.

82
00:13:00,197 --> 00:13:01,323
I'm sorry!

83
00:13:42,072 --> 00:13:43,157
They went that way!

84
00:13:49,246 --> 00:13:50,080
You can...

85
00:13:50,998 --> 00:13:51,999
transform.

86
00:13:52,374 --> 00:13:53,375
You're her.

87
00:13:53,542 --> 00:13:54,793
- The hero.
- I'm nobody.

88
00:13:54,960 --> 00:13:55,961
I'm not a hero.

89
00:13:56,128 --> 00:13:57,087
Let's get out of here.

90
00:14:19,943 --> 00:14:21,028
Have a good night, Henryk.

91
00:14:21,111 --> 00:14:22,446
You too, Milosz.

92
00:14:52,184 --> 00:14:53,185
Hi Honey.

93
00:14:53,644 --> 00:14:54,477
Hi.

94
00:14:58,774 --> 00:15:00,150
Good day?

95
00:15:00,317 --> 00:15:01,485
Better now.

96
00:15:02,194 --> 00:15:03,195
Where's Nina?

97
00:15:03,362 --> 00:15:05,614
Out back. With her friends.

98
00:15:34,351 --> 00:15:36,645
Where did you learn that song, Papa?

99
00:15:38,230 --> 00:15:40,357
I learned it from my parents.

100
00:15:41,316 --> 00:15:43,360
And they learned it from their parents.

101
00:15:44,361 --> 00:15:46,363
And them from theirs.

102
00:15:47,197 --> 00:15:48,657
And one day...

103
00:15:49,032 --> 00:15:51,368
you'll sing it to your children, too.

104
00:15:53,078 --> 00:15:54,371
What happened to them?

105
00:15:54,538 --> 00:15:55,747
Your parents.

106
00:15:59,501 --> 00:16:01,378
They were taken from me...

107
00:16:01,879 --> 00:16:03,380
when I was a little boy.

108
00:16:06,884 --> 00:16:08,260
But they're still here.

109
00:16:09,094 --> 00:16:10,262
Inside.

110
00:16:12,639 --> 00:16:14,057
And here.

111
00:16:15,392 --> 00:16:16,393
With you.

112
00:16:16,894 --> 00:16:20,063
Is someone going to take you away?

113
00:16:21,482 --> 00:16:23,400
Never.

114
00:16:39,416 --> 00:16:41,418
I guess we're more alike than we thought.

115
00:16:41,585 --> 00:16:42,961
He won't listen to us.

116
00:16:43,462 --> 00:16:44,922
He's just... He's being...

117
00:16:45,088 --> 00:16:46,173
Scott.

118
00:16:49,510 --> 00:16:50,511
Let me try.

119
00:17:05,359 --> 00:17:06,985
{\an8}<i>Smells pretty old in here.</i>

120
00:17:07,069 --> 00:17:08,695
Is this a school or a museum?

121
00:17:08,779 --> 00:17:11,448
One more. And last one.

122
00:17:11,740 --> 00:17:13,075
There you go.

123
00:17:14,243 --> 00:17:15,244
I'll see you guys.

124
00:17:25,128 --> 00:17:26,380
<i>Watch where you're going.</i>

125
00:17:26,547 --> 00:17:27,548
I can't.

126
00:17:28,840 --> 00:17:29,841
Who are you talking to?

127
00:17:30,008 --> 00:17:30,968
Me.

128
00:17:33,178 --> 00:17:34,429
I just heard you in my head.

129
00:17:35,347 --> 00:17:37,015
I'm telepathic. I read minds.

130
00:17:37,182 --> 00:17:38,183
Well, stay out of mine.

131
00:17:38,350 --> 00:17:40,470
I don't need some weird girl
creeping around in there.

132
00:17:41,270 --> 00:17:43,021
Don't worry, Scott.
There's not much to see.

133
00:17:44,356 --> 00:17:46,483
Hey, wait.
I didn't tell you my name.

134
00:17:46,650 --> 00:17:48,193
No, you didn't.

135
00:17:49,278 --> 00:17:50,571
Alex Summers?

136
00:17:51,321 --> 00:17:52,656
Hank McCoy!

137
00:17:52,823 --> 00:17:55,534
Whoa! What happened to the
big, blue, furry you?

138
00:17:55,701 --> 00:17:57,494
I keep him under control now.

139
00:17:59,162 --> 00:18:00,414
This is my brother, Scott.

140
00:18:00,581 --> 00:18:03,083
Hey, Scott. I'm Hank McCoy.
I'm one of the teachers here.

141
00:18:05,627 --> 00:18:06,920
Where's the professor?

142
00:18:07,296 --> 00:18:10,757
"To break forth bloodily,
then the past must be obliterated...

143
00:18:11,258 --> 00:18:13,385
"and a new start made.

144
00:18:13,552 --> 00:18:15,053
"Let us now start fresh...

145
00:18:15,220 --> 00:18:17,139
"without remembrance...

146
00:18:17,306 --> 00:18:21,518
"rather than live forward and backward
at the same time."

147
00:18:21,685 --> 00:18:24,980
Now, what on earth do we think
that the author meant...

148
00:18:25,147 --> 00:18:26,523
when he wrote all that?

149
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:31,445
That's going to be
your assignment for tomorrow.

150
00:18:31,612 --> 00:18:33,780
Top marks, everyone.
Class dismissed.

151
00:18:35,115 --> 00:18:35,948
Alex.

152
00:18:36,074 --> 00:18:38,076
- It's good to see you.
- You too.

153
00:18:38,243 --> 00:18:39,661
You look well. It's been a while.

154
00:18:39,828 --> 00:18:41,288
It has. Not too bad yourself.

155
00:18:41,455 --> 00:18:42,497
Thank you.

156
00:18:43,165 --> 00:18:44,249
This is my brother, Scott.

157
00:18:45,584 --> 00:18:48,462
Hello, Scott.
Welcome to the School for the Gifted.

158
00:18:49,129 --> 00:18:50,964
Yeah. It doesn't exactly feel like a gift.

159
00:18:51,840 --> 00:18:53,842
It never does, at first.

160
00:18:56,720 --> 00:18:58,930
The first step in
understanding one's power...

161
00:18:59,097 --> 00:19:00,932
is learning the extent of it.

162
00:19:01,099 --> 00:19:04,186
Only then can we begin the process
of teaching you how to control it.

163
00:19:04,353 --> 00:19:07,147
If you do decide to stay,
I can promise you...

164
00:19:07,314 --> 00:19:11,318
that by the time you're done here, you'll
be able to go back into the world...

165
00:19:11,485 --> 00:19:13,245
and play a stable and
productive part in it.

166
00:19:13,362 --> 00:19:14,714
Why don't you take your bandages off...

167
00:19:14,738 --> 00:19:17,282
and we can have a look
at what we're dealing with here?

168
00:19:17,449 --> 00:19:20,744
Alex, would you line him up? Face
him in the right direction, as it were.

169
00:19:20,911 --> 00:19:22,471
There's a target just across the water.

170
00:19:22,537 --> 00:19:24,217
When you open your eyes, try and hit that.

171
00:19:28,085 --> 00:19:29,419
You can open your eyes, Scott.

172
00:19:30,128 --> 00:19:32,297
There's nothing to be afraid of.
It's quite...

173
00:19:38,553 --> 00:19:40,097
Look out! Get back!

174
00:19:40,263 --> 00:19:41,640
Get back! Get back!

175
00:19:47,104 --> 00:19:49,940
My grandfather planted that tree
when he was five years old.

176
00:19:50,107 --> 00:19:51,316
I used to swing...

177
00:19:51,483 --> 00:19:53,527
from the branches of it, myself.

178
00:19:57,698 --> 00:19:59,378
I think that was probably
my favorite tree.

179
00:20:00,367 --> 00:20:02,202
Does that mean I'm expelled?

180
00:20:02,369 --> 00:20:03,578
On the contrary.

181
00:20:04,996 --> 00:20:06,123
You're enrolled.

182
00:20:55,672 --> 00:20:57,174
Do you sell rugs?

183
00:20:57,382 --> 00:20:59,509
You're not allowed in this area.

184
00:20:59,676 --> 00:21:01,386
This rug is for sale?

185
00:21:01,678 --> 00:21:02,511
I said, this --

186
00:25:04,671 --> 00:25:05,588
Earthquake!

187
00:25:52,385 --> 00:25:54,030
Back to bed, please, my darling.
Back to bed.

188
00:25:54,054 --> 00:25:55,055
She's doing it again.

189
00:25:55,221 --> 00:25:57,098
Back to bed, please, everyone.

190
00:25:57,265 --> 00:25:58,391
Jesse, back to bed, please.

191
00:25:58,558 --> 00:26:00,060
Come on now. Spit-spot, back to bed.

192
00:26:00,226 --> 00:26:01,770
Carrie Anne, come on now. Back to bed.

193
00:26:10,445 --> 00:26:12,113
Never seen it like this.

194
00:26:12,280 --> 00:26:13,490
Nor I.

195
00:26:14,616 --> 00:26:16,451
Don't let any of the children
come this way.

196
00:26:37,138 --> 00:26:38,139
Jean.

197
00:26:59,661 --> 00:27:00,620
Jean!

198
00:27:03,206 --> 00:27:04,874
Jean!

199
00:27:13,299 --> 00:27:15,468
I saw the end of the world.

200
00:27:16,219 --> 00:27:17,554
I could feel...

201
00:27:17,720 --> 00:27:19,889
all this death.

202
00:27:22,183 --> 00:27:23,560
It was just a dream.

203
00:27:23,726 --> 00:27:25,395
No, it felt real.

204
00:27:25,562 --> 00:27:26,563
I know.

205
00:27:27,063 --> 00:27:30,191
Your mind is the most powerful
I've ever seen.

206
00:27:30,525 --> 00:27:31,651
It can convince itself...

207
00:27:31,818 --> 00:27:33,528
No, no...

208
00:27:33,695 --> 00:27:35,735
It's not just the mind-reading
or the telekinesis...

209
00:27:35,822 --> 00:27:37,323
it's something else.

210
00:27:40,577 --> 00:27:43,538
Some dark power inside and it's growing.

211
00:27:43,705 --> 00:27:45,081
Like a fire.

212
00:27:46,416 --> 00:27:47,709
I thought I was getting better.

213
00:27:47,876 --> 00:27:48,918
You are.

214
00:27:49,085 --> 00:27:50,420
You will.

215
00:27:51,212 --> 00:27:52,332
You just have to be patient.

216
00:27:52,422 --> 00:27:55,842
No, no. You don't know what it's like
to be afraid to shut your eyes.

217
00:27:56,009 --> 00:27:58,428
To be trapped inside your own head.

218
00:27:58,595 --> 00:28:00,388
Oh, I think I do.

219
00:28:00,889 --> 00:28:04,267
It wasn't so long ago that
I was plagued by voices, myself.

220
00:28:05,226 --> 00:28:06,728
All their suffering.

221
00:28:06,895 --> 00:28:07,937
All their pain.

222
00:28:08,771 --> 00:28:10,273
Their secrets.

223
00:28:13,776 --> 00:28:16,696
I'm afraid one day
I'm going to hurt someone.

224
00:28:19,782 --> 00:28:21,284
Lie back.

225
00:28:31,419 --> 00:28:34,964
Everyone fears that
which they do not understand.

226
00:28:37,050 --> 00:28:39,636
You will learn to control your powers.

227
00:28:39,802 --> 00:28:41,638
And when you do...

228
00:28:42,305 --> 00:28:44,140
you'll have nothing to fear.

229
00:28:46,559 --> 00:28:48,159
Her nightmares were different this time.

230
00:28:48,269 --> 00:28:51,147
It could account for something I saw
when I was in my lab earlier.

231
00:28:51,314 --> 00:28:53,399
There was some kind of tremor.
Like an energy surge.

232
00:28:53,566 --> 00:28:55,151
I picked it up on one of my meters.

233
00:28:55,318 --> 00:28:57,445
You're saying Jean created it?

234
00:28:57,612 --> 00:28:59,113
No. I'm saying something else did.

235
00:28:59,280 --> 00:29:00,960
Maybe she was reacting to it.
I don't know.

236
00:29:01,074 --> 00:29:02,951
But the epicenter was
halfway around the world.

237
00:29:03,117 --> 00:29:04,244
Halfway around the world?

238
00:29:04,410 --> 00:29:06,138
That's why I was hoping you could
take a look.

239
00:29:06,162 --> 00:29:08,164
Let's see what we can find.

240
00:29:10,667 --> 00:29:12,126
<i>Welcome, Professor.</i>

241
00:29:22,929 --> 00:29:24,847
Okay, the source came from Cairo.

242
00:29:27,016 --> 00:29:28,351
I'll put in the coordinates.

243
00:29:53,209 --> 00:29:54,711
<i>I gotta get out of here.</i>

244
00:29:55,545 --> 00:29:56,546
<i>Give them a report.</i>

245
00:29:59,215 --> 00:30:00,300
What? What is it?

246
00:30:00,466 --> 00:30:03,886
<i>Something happened here.
I can tell them it's real.</i>

247
00:30:05,388 --> 00:30:06,389
It's her.

248
00:30:06,973 --> 00:30:07,806
Who?

249
00:30:09,225 --> 00:30:10,518
- Moira.
- What?

250
00:30:10,685 --> 00:30:11,894
Moira MacTaggert?

251
00:30:12,687 --> 00:30:14,230
Give me the details.

252
00:30:14,397 --> 00:30:16,316
She looks amazing.
She's barely aged a day.

253
00:30:16,649 --> 00:30:18,067
No. I meant...

254
00:30:18,693 --> 00:30:19,694
What is she doing there?

255
00:30:19,861 --> 00:30:21,181
What does the CIA want with this?

256
00:30:21,571 --> 00:30:24,574
She's going back to Langley
to deliver a report.

257
00:30:25,408 --> 00:30:26,409
I'm going to go there...

258
00:30:26,576 --> 00:30:28,911
see if she knows something
about the tremor.

259
00:30:29,078 --> 00:30:30,246
And you want to go see Moira.

260
00:30:30,830 --> 00:30:32,540
I want to go check her out.
Check out...

261
00:30:32,707 --> 00:30:33,833
the situation.

262
00:30:37,587 --> 00:30:38,588
Moira MacTaggert.

263
00:30:41,382 --> 00:30:43,092
It's like a ghost from the past.

264
00:30:46,220 --> 00:30:47,820
You did a good thing.
You saved that man.

265
00:30:47,930 --> 00:30:49,098
That's not the point.

266
00:30:49,891 --> 00:30:51,251
If I'm exposed, we're all exposed.

267
00:30:51,434 --> 00:30:52,435
{\an8}We have to go.

268
00:30:53,936 --> 00:30:55,396
This is our home.

269
00:30:55,563 --> 00:30:57,273
This is our daughter's home.

270
00:30:57,440 --> 00:30:59,359
We are her home.

271
00:31:01,027 --> 00:31:03,946
I told you who I was,
the first night I met you.

272
00:31:04,447 --> 00:31:06,115
I trusted you then.

273
00:31:06,282 --> 00:31:08,284
I need you to trust me now.

274
00:31:09,369 --> 00:31:11,454
We can't stay here anymore.

275
00:31:16,459 --> 00:31:17,418
I'll get Nina.

276
00:31:20,296 --> 00:31:21,547
Sweetheart.

277
00:31:32,475 --> 00:31:34,060
She's not in her room.

278
00:31:34,227 --> 00:31:35,645
And I don't see her out back.

279
00:31:43,778 --> 00:31:44,821
Nina?

280
00:31:44,987 --> 00:31:46,239
Nina!

281
00:31:46,489 --> 00:31:47,323
Nina!

282
00:31:47,573 --> 00:31:48,408
Nina!

283
00:31:54,288 --> 00:31:55,665
Nina!

284
00:32:16,978 --> 00:32:18,020
Nina.

285
00:32:18,104 --> 00:32:19,689
Are you alright?

286
00:32:19,981 --> 00:32:21,232
She's fine.

287
00:32:21,315 --> 00:32:22,567
Then let her go!

288
00:32:22,650 --> 00:32:23,818
We will.

289
00:32:24,652 --> 00:32:26,863
We just wanted to have a word

290
00:32:29,615 --> 00:32:31,868
You're not wearing your badges.

291
00:32:32,326 --> 00:32:34,328
No metal.

292
00:32:35,163 --> 00:32:37,832
Some guys at the factory said
they saw something today.

293
00:32:38,082 --> 00:32:40,460
Something that didn't add up.

294
00:32:40,543 --> 00:32:42,128
Put your weapons away.

295
00:32:42,211 --> 00:32:44,630
You've been a good citizen, Henryk...

296
00:32:44,881 --> 00:32:47,049
A good neighbor... a good worker.

297
00:32:47,383 --> 00:32:49,135
I want to believe that's who you are.

298
00:32:49,218 --> 00:32:50,303
It is.

299
00:32:50,386 --> 00:32:53,139
But nobody in this town really knows you.

300
00:32:53,222 --> 00:32:54,765
Yes you do.

301
00:32:55,558 --> 00:32:57,435
I am Henryk Gurzsky.

302
00:32:57,643 --> 00:33:00,021
Jakob, I've had dinner in your home...

303
00:33:00,146 --> 00:33:02,190
And you were lying the whole time.

304
00:33:02,440 --> 00:33:04,609
I brought a killer into my house.

305
00:33:06,861 --> 00:33:09,322
Is this you?

306
00:33:13,117 --> 00:33:16,037
Are you the one they call Magneto?

307
00:33:36,307 --> 00:33:38,476
Take me in.

308
00:33:38,976 --> 00:33:39,809
Please...

309
00:33:39,852 --> 00:33:42,522
Just let my daughter go.

310
00:33:52,365 --> 00:33:53,824
Go with your mother.

311
00:34:02,208 --> 00:34:03,417
Please...!

312
00:34:04,585 --> 00:34:06,337
Don't leave me.

313
00:34:06,921 --> 00:34:09,423
I'm not going to let them take you.

314
00:34:09,757 --> 00:34:10,758
Nina.

315
00:34:12,635 --> 00:34:13,886
Nina.

316
00:34:14,804 --> 00:34:15,805
Nina.

317
00:34:16,889 --> 00:34:17,807
What's going on?

318
00:34:18,474 --> 00:34:19,433
She's one of them?

319
00:34:21,852 --> 00:34:22,812
Tell her to stop!

320
00:34:22,895 --> 00:34:24,522
She can't control it!

321
00:34:25,690 --> 00:34:26,941
She's scared of you!

322
00:34:27,275 --> 00:34:29,151
I'm not going to let them take you!

323
00:34:36,450 --> 00:34:37,577
Make her stop!

324
00:34:39,412 --> 00:34:41,038
Nina! Nina!

325
00:35:02,768 --> 00:35:03,601
Nina.

326
00:35:03,686 --> 00:35:05,605
Nina, Nina, no...

327
00:35:05,771 --> 00:35:07,898
No, please. Please!

328
00:35:10,776 --> 00:35:11,777
Please.

329
00:35:12,486 --> 00:35:13,696
Please.

330
00:35:21,787 --> 00:35:23,497
Not my babies.

331
00:35:28,794 --> 00:35:30,588
Not my babies.

332
00:36:13,339 --> 00:36:15,049
Is this what you want from me?

333
00:36:17,968 --> 00:36:19,428
Is this what I am?

334
00:36:27,019 --> 00:36:28,562
Is this what I am?

335
00:37:44,472 --> 00:37:46,348
You know what we do to thieves.

336
00:37:46,974 --> 00:37:48,225
Pick a hand.

337
00:37:48,392 --> 00:37:49,518
Enough.

338
00:37:52,354 --> 00:37:54,356
If you're with her,
I suggest you walk away.

339
00:37:54,607 --> 00:37:55,983
While you still can.

340
00:37:58,694 --> 00:37:59,653
Walk away

341
00:38:01,197 --> 00:38:05,034
Who rules this world?

342
00:38:05,618 --> 00:38:07,328
What language is that?

343
00:38:09,955 --> 00:38:12,374
Clown-face. What's the deal?

344
00:38:12,458 --> 00:38:13,584
Beat it!

345
00:38:29,225 --> 00:38:30,726
I'm sorry.

346
00:38:36,816 --> 00:38:40,069
You can't feel it, can you?

347
00:38:52,373 --> 00:38:55,125
Now you feel it.

348
00:39:04,552 --> 00:39:06,512
So you really haven't seen her
in all these years?

349
00:39:06,554 --> 00:39:08,889
You never looked her up?
Not even in Cerebro?

350
00:39:09,515 --> 00:39:12,184
Alex! What do you take me for,
some kind of pervert?

351
00:39:12,351 --> 00:39:14,186
Yes, I looked her up once. Twice.

352
00:39:14,353 --> 00:39:15,938
But not in a long time, all right?

353
00:39:16,105 --> 00:39:18,315
How did you leave things?
Any hard feelings?

354
00:39:18,816 --> 00:39:19,817
Not likely.

355
00:39:19,984 --> 00:39:21,569
Everybody take a break.

356
00:39:23,153 --> 00:39:25,865
I wiped her mind of all memories of us.

357
00:39:26,031 --> 00:39:27,950
The beach, Cuba...

358
00:39:28,117 --> 00:39:29,827
that whole time.

359
00:39:29,994 --> 00:39:31,328
It was so long ago, Alex.

360
00:39:31,495 --> 00:39:33,080
Before the world knew about mutants.

361
00:39:33,247 --> 00:39:36,208
I felt it was the best thing for her.

362
00:39:36,792 --> 00:39:38,586
And for you?

363
00:39:40,588 --> 00:39:43,090
Didn't really matter what was best for me.

364
00:39:46,427 --> 00:39:48,095
Moira...

365
00:39:48,262 --> 00:39:49,972
MacTaggert, hello!

366
00:39:54,810 --> 00:39:56,145
Allow me to introduce myself.

367
00:39:56,312 --> 00:39:58,105
- I'm Professor...
- Charles Xavier.

368
00:39:58,272 --> 00:40:00,482
- I know exactly who you are.
- You do?

369
00:40:00,649 --> 00:40:01,650
Of course I do.

370
00:40:02,318 --> 00:40:04,820
I have read all of your papers.

371
00:40:04,987 --> 00:40:06,989
It's a pleasure to finally meet you.

372
00:40:08,157 --> 00:40:09,116
Moira MacTaggert.

373
00:40:09,283 --> 00:40:10,451
- Alex Summers.
- Have a seat.

374
00:40:10,618 --> 00:40:12,286
Just throw that on the floor.

375
00:40:13,662 --> 00:40:15,372
It's wonderful to see you again.

376
00:40:15,539 --> 00:40:17,666
To meet you again, for the first time.

377
00:40:17,833 --> 00:40:18,834
You've got a son?

378
00:40:20,836 --> 00:40:22,338
Yes.

379
00:40:22,504 --> 00:40:23,756
Does he have a husband?

380
00:40:25,966 --> 00:40:27,301
Do you have a husband?

381
00:40:27,468 --> 00:40:29,428
I had a husband...

382
00:40:29,595 --> 00:40:32,155
but it's hard to do this job
and make it home in time for dinner.

383
00:40:32,181 --> 00:40:33,015
Good, good.

384
00:40:33,182 --> 00:40:34,600
We all make choices, right?

385
00:40:35,184 --> 00:40:37,102
Yes, we do.

386
00:40:39,188 --> 00:40:41,357
- Professor.
- Yes?

387
00:40:42,316 --> 00:40:43,275
Yes.

388
00:40:43,525 --> 00:40:46,028
I was, we were hoping that you would...

389
00:40:46,195 --> 00:40:48,322
tell us about what happened
yesterday in Egypt.

390
00:40:49,031 --> 00:40:51,116
I'm afraid that's classified information.

391
00:40:52,368 --> 00:40:54,370
I don't mean to be rude...

392
00:40:54,995 --> 00:40:56,538
but how did you get in here?

393
00:40:57,122 --> 00:40:58,874
I have level-five clearance.

394
00:41:01,335 --> 00:41:04,213
Ever since the world found out
about mutants in '73...

395
00:41:04,380 --> 00:41:07,216
there have been cults
who see them as some kind of...

396
00:41:07,383 --> 00:41:09,385
Second Coming or sign of God.

397
00:41:09,551 --> 00:41:10,844
I was tracking one of them.

398
00:41:11,553 --> 00:41:15,057
They call themselves Ashir En Sabah Nur...

399
00:41:15,224 --> 00:41:18,394
named after an ancient being
they believe to be the world's first.

400
00:41:18,560 --> 00:41:19,853
The world's first what?

401
00:41:20,020 --> 00:41:21,397
The world's first mutant.

402
00:41:21,730 --> 00:41:24,316
I thought mutants didn't evolve
until this century.

403
00:41:24,483 --> 00:41:26,819
That's the common theory, yes,
but these guys believe...

404
00:41:26,986 --> 00:41:30,322
that the first mutant was born
tens of thousands of years ago.

405
00:41:30,489 --> 00:41:31,841
And they believe he will rise again.

406
00:41:31,865 --> 00:41:35,244
They've been searching ancient sites
all around the world for clues.

407
00:41:36,578 --> 00:41:37,746
These hieroglyphs...

408
00:41:37,913 --> 00:41:41,875
describe a specific set of powers
greater than any man could possess.

409
00:41:42,042 --> 00:41:43,544
They think he lived all that time?

410
00:41:43,711 --> 00:41:46,505
Yes and no.
They believe he had the ability...

411
00:41:46,672 --> 00:41:48,316
to transfer his consciousness
from body to body.

412
00:41:48,340 --> 00:41:49,820
And whenever he was close to death...

413
00:41:49,925 --> 00:41:51,343
he would just take on a new body.

414
00:41:51,510 --> 00:41:53,550
Some of these may have been
the bodies of mutants...

415
00:41:53,679 --> 00:41:55,431
enabling him to take their powers...

416
00:41:55,597 --> 00:41:57,433
amassing various abilities over the years.

417
00:41:57,599 --> 00:42:00,269
- An all-powerful mutant.
- Exactly.

418
00:42:00,436 --> 00:42:03,230
And wherever this being was
he always had four...

419
00:42:03,397 --> 00:42:06,233
principle followers.
Disciples.

420
00:42:06,400 --> 00:42:08,277
Protectors he would imbue with powers.

421
00:42:08,444 --> 00:42:09,570
Like the Four Horsemen...

422
00:42:10,279 --> 00:42:11,947
of the Apocalypse.

423
00:42:12,114 --> 00:42:13,699
He got that one from the Bible.

424
00:42:13,866 --> 00:42:15,617
Or the Bible got it from him.

425
00:42:16,285 --> 00:42:17,911
And wherever he ruled...

426
00:42:18,078 --> 00:42:20,956
eventually, it would end in disaster.

427
00:42:21,123 --> 00:42:22,416
Cataclysm.

428
00:42:22,583 --> 00:42:24,626
Some kind of...

429
00:42:24,793 --> 00:42:26,253
Apocalypse.

430
00:42:27,296 --> 00:42:29,048
The end of the world.

431
00:42:30,758 --> 00:42:32,634
<i>I must say, Apollo...</i>

432
00:42:33,635 --> 00:42:36,138
<i>the way you ape human behavior
is remarkable.</i>

433
00:42:42,644 --> 00:42:43,687
<i>I am Apollo.</i>

434
00:42:43,771 --> 00:42:46,774
I've never seen another
mutant in this town.

435
00:42:47,066 --> 00:42:48,525
You speak Egyptian?

436
00:42:48,692 --> 00:42:49,525
Arabic?

437
00:42:50,152 --> 00:42:51,278
English?

438
00:42:51,445 --> 00:42:52,988
<i>I'm a scientist.</i>

439
00:42:53,155 --> 00:42:54,490
<i>My particular specialty...</i>

440
00:42:54,656 --> 00:42:55,657
Great fighter.

441
00:42:57,743 --> 00:42:58,911
She's my hero.

442
00:42:59,078 --> 00:43:00,954
I want to be like her.

443
00:43:03,499 --> 00:43:06,502
There's some food here. Not much.

444
00:43:06,668 --> 00:43:07,753
<i>I don't believe it.</i>

445
00:43:07,920 --> 00:43:09,296
<i>You love me.</i>

446
00:43:10,172 --> 00:43:11,173
<i>Love you?</i>

447
00:43:12,007 --> 00:43:12,840
<i>Illogical.</i>

448
00:43:13,842 --> 00:43:16,845
<i>I'm not some simple shepherdess
you can awe.</i>

449
00:43:18,180 --> 00:43:20,474
<i>Why, I could no more love you...</i>

450
00:43:20,641 --> 00:43:23,602
<i>than I could love a new species
of bacteria.</i>

451
00:43:24,812 --> 00:43:26,271
What are you doing?

452
00:43:28,190 --> 00:43:30,359
Learning.

453
00:43:38,200 --> 00:43:41,620
<i>In the streets, there is outrage against
the Soviet invasion of Afghanistan...</i>

454
00:43:42,121 --> 00:43:43,264
<i>...in a brotherhood of our kind.</i>

455
00:43:43,288 --> 00:43:44,208
<i>Several demonstrations.</i>

456
00:43:45,791 --> 00:43:48,794
<i>One of them was held in Boston,
and Bruce Morton has the story.</i>

457
00:43:48,961 --> 00:43:52,840
<i>Since the advent of nuclear weapons,
the United States does not start fights.</i>

458
00:43:53,465 --> 00:43:54,716
Weapons.

459
00:43:54,883 --> 00:43:57,636
<i>Never before has man
possessed so much power.</i>

460
00:43:57,803 --> 00:44:00,222
<i>Soviet Union and
United States being superpowers...</i>

461
00:44:01,974 --> 00:44:04,810
Superpowers.

462
00:44:05,686 --> 00:44:07,396
The weak...

463
00:44:07,563 --> 00:44:09,731
have taken the earth.

464
00:44:10,399 --> 00:44:13,443
For this, I was betrayed.

465
00:44:13,819 --> 00:44:16,155
False gods.

466
00:44:17,156 --> 00:44:18,073
Idols.

467
00:44:19,908 --> 00:44:22,619
No more.

468
00:44:25,414 --> 00:44:29,418
I have returned.

469
00:44:30,127 --> 00:44:32,212
<i>A new tomorrow...</i>

470
00:44:32,379 --> 00:44:33,922
{\an8}<i>that starts today.</i>

471
00:44:38,927 --> 00:44:40,637
Where did you come from?

472
00:44:47,519 --> 00:44:50,772
A time before man lost his way.

473
00:44:53,859 --> 00:44:55,777
Welcome to the '80s.

474
00:44:55,986 --> 00:44:58,780
This world needs to be...

475
00:45:00,449 --> 00:45:02,201
Cleansed.

476
00:45:02,993 --> 00:45:03,952
What?

477
00:45:04,912 --> 00:45:06,413
Saved.

478
00:45:08,332 --> 00:45:10,459
You can't save the world...

479
00:45:10,626 --> 00:45:12,586
just going around killing people.

480
00:45:12,753 --> 00:45:14,421
There's laws, systems in place...

481
00:45:14,588 --> 00:45:15,714
for that kind of thing.

482
00:45:18,634 --> 00:45:19,843
My child...

483
00:45:20,010 --> 00:45:22,638
why do you enslave yourself?

484
00:45:27,351 --> 00:45:29,061
What are you doing?

485
00:45:29,228 --> 00:45:30,812
Making you stronger.

486
00:45:32,189 --> 00:45:34,107
My goddess.

487
00:45:40,906 --> 00:45:41,949
<i>Aphrodite.</i>

488
00:45:43,283 --> 00:45:44,243
<i>You were right.</i>

489
00:45:44,409 --> 00:45:45,577
Yes.

490
00:45:49,289 --> 00:45:50,749
<i>You were right.</i>

491
00:45:51,416 --> 00:45:53,293
<i>The time is past.</i>

492
00:45:54,169 --> 00:45:56,338
<i>There is no room for gods.</i>

493
00:46:00,884 --> 00:46:02,386
Why can't I go with you?

494
00:46:02,552 --> 00:46:04,179
I told you, I work alone.

495
00:46:11,270 --> 00:46:12,562
Wait there.

496
00:46:13,939 --> 00:46:16,024
Always good to see your face.

497
00:46:16,191 --> 00:46:17,234
Even if it's not yours.

498
00:46:18,402 --> 00:46:19,611
Papers and passage for one.

499
00:46:21,989 --> 00:46:24,324
Where's the gentleman going, if I may ask?

500
00:46:24,491 --> 00:46:25,617
Don't know, don't care.

501
00:46:26,576 --> 00:46:28,776
I just save his life.
What he does with it is up to him.

502
00:46:28,954 --> 00:46:31,456
Mystique, the mercenary.

503
00:46:31,623 --> 00:46:32,874
Don't call me that.

504
00:46:33,041 --> 00:46:34,519
No matter how much you pretend
to be someone else...

505
00:46:34,543 --> 00:46:36,003
Caliban knows who you are.

506
00:46:36,169 --> 00:46:38,338
If there's anything worth knowing
about mutants...

507
00:46:38,505 --> 00:46:40,007
Caliban knows it.

508
00:46:40,507 --> 00:46:41,550
Mystique.

509
00:46:42,259 --> 00:46:43,403
Why don't you ask your psychics...

510
00:46:43,427 --> 00:46:45,387
what'll happen to you
if you keep pushing me?

511
00:46:45,554 --> 00:46:46,388
What'll happen?

512
00:46:50,851 --> 00:46:52,644
Psylocke gets a little jealous.

513
00:46:54,813 --> 00:46:56,064
But Caliban likes you.

514
00:46:56,231 --> 00:46:57,482
Caliban likes money.

515
00:46:57,649 --> 00:46:59,526
Caliban likes you so much...

516
00:46:59,693 --> 00:47:01,862
he wants to give you free information...

517
00:47:02,029 --> 00:47:03,989
about an old friend...

518
00:47:04,156 --> 00:47:05,615
from back when you had friends.

519
00:47:06,158 --> 00:47:08,618
Do you remember...

520
00:47:08,785 --> 00:47:10,829
Erik Lehnsherr?

521
00:47:11,121 --> 00:47:13,123
My girls got a flash of him in Poland.

522
00:47:13,290 --> 00:47:15,250
He left quite a few dead bodies
in his wake...

523
00:47:15,584 --> 00:47:18,295
including his wife and daughter.

524
00:47:18,795 --> 00:47:21,465
Should be in the news soon enough...

525
00:47:22,090 --> 00:47:23,770
but Caliban gives you a little head start.

526
00:47:25,469 --> 00:47:27,429
- How fast are you?
- How fast?

527
00:47:27,596 --> 00:47:29,139
How far can you cover?

528
00:47:29,306 --> 00:47:31,117
As far as I can see
or if I've been there before.

529
00:47:31,141 --> 00:47:32,476
Come with me, Crawler.

530
00:47:32,642 --> 00:47:34,102
Actually, it's Nightcrawler.

531
00:47:34,269 --> 00:47:36,188
And my real name is...

532
00:47:37,564 --> 00:47:39,358
Kurt Wagner.

533
00:47:43,528 --> 00:47:46,114
The lenses are made of
some ruby quartz I had lying around.

534
00:47:46,281 --> 00:47:48,176
They should be able to
refract your optic beams...

535
00:47:48,200 --> 00:47:50,360
and keep them contained
within their own vector fields.

536
00:47:50,410 --> 00:47:51,620
Try them on.

537
00:48:06,259 --> 00:48:07,092
Okay.

538
00:48:07,135 --> 00:48:09,096
Go ahead.

539
00:48:09,971 --> 00:48:11,973
Wait, sorry, no.

540
00:48:12,140 --> 00:48:13,016
Okay.

541
00:48:13,183 --> 00:48:14,223
- Now?
- Yeah, you're good.

542
00:48:14,267 --> 00:48:15,268
All right.

543
00:48:19,356 --> 00:48:20,357
Whoa.

544
00:48:21,817 --> 00:48:23,360
I can see.

545
00:48:23,527 --> 00:48:24,736
Thank you.

546
00:48:25,153 --> 00:48:27,030
Professor, thank you. You're a genius.

547
00:48:27,197 --> 00:48:28,156
No.

548
00:48:28,615 --> 00:48:31,034
I'm not a professor.
I wish...

549
00:48:32,828 --> 00:48:33,829
Who's that?

550
00:48:36,665 --> 00:48:38,333
I believe you two met. That's Jean Grey.

551
00:48:38,500 --> 00:48:39,894
You bumped into her when you arrived.

552
00:48:39,918 --> 00:48:41,837
- Wait, that's her?
- Yeah.

553
00:48:47,259 --> 00:48:48,093
Hey.

554
00:48:51,138 --> 00:48:52,264
You can see.

555
00:48:53,682 --> 00:48:56,017
Yeah. It's not as bad as I thought here.

556
00:48:56,184 --> 00:48:57,144
Freak.

557
00:48:57,310 --> 00:48:58,788
- Someone should warn the new kid.
- Yeah. Someone should tell him.

558
00:48:58,812 --> 00:49:00,105
They're still scared of me.

559
00:49:00,522 --> 00:49:02,357
Hey, I have special glasses now.

560
00:49:02,524 --> 00:49:03,817
They're not scared of you.

561
00:49:03,984 --> 00:49:05,694
They're scared of me.

562
00:49:06,278 --> 00:49:09,614
You're not the only one who
can't fully control your powers.

563
00:49:10,615 --> 00:49:11,616
Wait, so...

564
00:49:11,783 --> 00:49:14,536
last night, when the house shook...

565
00:49:15,036 --> 00:49:16,037
that was you?

566
00:49:16,204 --> 00:49:19,084
Sorry to break it to you, but you're not
the biggest freak in the school.

567
00:49:19,791 --> 00:49:21,626
Well, that's a first.

568
00:49:35,515 --> 00:49:36,850
Raven.

569
00:49:41,313 --> 00:49:42,314
Wow.

570
00:49:43,648 --> 00:49:45,400
I... You're...

571
00:49:45,567 --> 00:49:46,735
Not blue?

572
00:49:46,902 --> 00:49:48,820
Looks like you and I
have that in common, now.

573
00:49:48,987 --> 00:49:51,072
No, no, I meant...

574
00:49:52,991 --> 00:49:54,201
you're back.

575
00:49:55,827 --> 00:49:57,746
Never thought I'd see you here again.

576
00:49:59,080 --> 00:50:00,499
Yeah, me neither.

577
00:50:03,835 --> 00:50:05,212
I'm blue.

578
00:50:05,670 --> 00:50:06,838
I'm Kurt.

579
00:50:07,005 --> 00:50:08,256
Oh, right.

580
00:50:08,590 --> 00:50:09,591
Kurt Wagner.

581
00:50:10,592 --> 00:50:11,426
Welcome.

582
00:50:14,888 --> 00:50:16,348
We're closed.

583
00:50:19,893 --> 00:50:21,895
I knew I felt a chill in the air.

584
00:50:24,773 --> 00:50:25,941
How did you get in here?

585
00:50:26,107 --> 00:50:27,108
We let ourselves in.

586
00:50:27,275 --> 00:50:28,777
We are looking for mutants.

587
00:50:28,944 --> 00:50:32,030
Since you know where to find them,
we came here.

588
00:50:32,197 --> 00:50:33,573
Caliban doesn't know you.

589
00:50:34,783 --> 00:50:37,410
We're looking for the strongest.

590
00:50:41,957 --> 00:50:43,083
Everything all right?

591
00:50:43,250 --> 00:50:44,459
I'm fine, Psylocke.

592
00:50:45,252 --> 00:50:46,962
How much money do you have?

593
00:50:47,462 --> 00:50:48,296
None.

594
00:50:49,631 --> 00:50:51,633
Like Caliban said...

595
00:50:51,800 --> 00:50:53,468
we are closed. Yeah?

596
00:50:55,095 --> 00:50:57,472
I need your help, my child.

597
00:50:58,431 --> 00:51:00,100
You don't look like Caliban's father.

598
00:51:00,809 --> 00:51:02,477
Maybe a little bit up here.

599
00:51:10,569 --> 00:51:12,445
You are all my children...

600
00:51:12,612 --> 00:51:15,949
and you're lost, because you follow
blind leaders.

601
00:51:16,783 --> 00:51:19,119
These false gods...

602
00:51:19,494 --> 00:51:21,997
systems of the weak.

603
00:51:22,455 --> 00:51:24,666
They've ruined my world...

604
00:51:25,166 --> 00:51:26,126
No more.

605
00:51:34,843 --> 00:51:36,678
What do you want?

606
00:51:46,521 --> 00:51:48,023
I want you...

607
00:51:48,648 --> 00:51:51,484
to feel the full reach of your power.

608
00:51:57,490 --> 00:52:00,619
You've only had a taste
of your true strength.

609
00:52:00,785 --> 00:52:02,037
Unlike others...

610
00:52:02,203 --> 00:52:04,539
who seek to control you...

611
00:52:05,040 --> 00:52:07,375
I want to set you free.

612
00:52:17,302 --> 00:52:19,512
I know the kind of mutants
you're looking for.

613
00:52:21,723 --> 00:52:24,059
And I know where to find them.

614
00:52:27,812 --> 00:52:29,314
<i>It's my first time in America.</i>

615
00:52:29,481 --> 00:52:31,358
I'm very excited to see your culture.

616
00:52:31,524 --> 00:52:33,193
Well, you're not gonna see it here.

617
00:52:33,360 --> 00:52:36,160
The only thing American about this place
is that it used to be British.

618
00:52:36,696 --> 00:52:37,739
This is Scott.

619
00:52:38,865 --> 00:52:40,241
He's new here, too.

620
00:52:40,408 --> 00:52:41,928
And I'm already up for a prison break.

621
00:52:44,245 --> 00:52:46,665
What do we say, we take this blue guy
on a little field trip?

622
00:52:46,831 --> 00:52:48,671
I'm sure there's a
mall around here, somewhere.

623
00:52:49,250 --> 00:52:50,418
What's a mall?

624
00:52:51,586 --> 00:52:52,587
What's a mall?

625
00:52:52,754 --> 00:52:55,590
All right, now this is a matter of
national pride. Civic duty.

626
00:52:55,757 --> 00:52:56,841
Scott.

627
00:52:57,842 --> 00:52:59,928
What? You've been cooped up here
for a long time...

628
00:53:00,261 --> 00:53:02,430
and the Professor's not even home.

629
00:53:03,223 --> 00:53:04,599
I'd like to go to the mall.

630
00:53:06,935 --> 00:53:08,103
Try it.

631
00:53:08,269 --> 00:53:09,102
All right.

632
00:53:10,021 --> 00:53:11,439
Where does he keep his cars?

633
00:53:26,413 --> 00:53:28,415
Or should I say "piss off"?

634
00:53:33,795 --> 00:53:34,963
This is the guy?

635
00:53:35,213 --> 00:53:36,631
He used to be.

636
00:53:36,798 --> 00:53:38,883
I didn't know his wings were...

637
00:53:42,887 --> 00:53:44,139
Let's get out of here.

638
00:53:44,431 --> 00:53:45,724
His fighting days are done.

639
00:53:46,558 --> 00:53:48,226
No, they're not.

640
00:53:53,940 --> 00:53:55,150
What the hell is this?

641
00:53:58,403 --> 00:53:59,988
I want to give you something.

642
00:54:00,321 --> 00:54:02,657
There's nothing you can give me
that I want.

643
00:54:03,408 --> 00:54:05,493
Yes, there is.

644
00:54:20,300 --> 00:54:22,302
Yes, my son.

645
00:54:36,107 --> 00:54:37,358
Yes.

646
00:54:49,037 --> 00:54:52,040
Rise, my angel.

647
00:54:54,876 --> 00:54:56,044
Rise.

648
00:55:25,949 --> 00:55:26,950
Wow.

649
00:55:29,077 --> 00:55:32,914
Hypersonic, blast resistant,
stealth technology.

650
00:55:33,081 --> 00:55:34,374
That's impressive.

651
00:55:34,874 --> 00:55:37,210
How are you ever gonna get it out of here?

652
00:55:38,586 --> 00:55:39,587
Well, that's okay.

653
00:55:39,754 --> 00:55:41,834
I built a retractable roof
into the basketball court.

654
00:55:43,216 --> 00:55:45,301
Hank, you're building a warplane
down here.

655
00:55:46,219 --> 00:55:48,948
After what happened in Washington,
I thought we were going to come back...

656
00:55:48,972 --> 00:55:51,057
and start the X-Men,
like we all used to talk about.

657
00:55:51,224 --> 00:55:52,475
But...

658
00:55:52,642 --> 00:55:54,602
Charles wants students, not soldiers.

659
00:55:55,103 --> 00:55:56,646
And he thinks the best of people.

660
00:55:56,813 --> 00:55:57,897
He has hope.

661
00:55:58,273 --> 00:55:59,440
And you?

662
00:56:00,775 --> 00:56:02,735
You know, I think we should
hope for the best.

663
00:56:02,902 --> 00:56:05,321
And prepare for the worst.

664
00:56:06,114 --> 00:56:07,657
I think the world needs the X-Men.

665
00:56:08,992 --> 00:56:12,579
And maybe now that you're back,
you could help me convince him.

666
00:56:12,745 --> 00:56:13,825
We could start it together.

667
00:56:13,913 --> 00:56:15,164
Hank, I'm here about Erik.

668
00:56:16,791 --> 00:56:18,418
Right. Erik.

669
00:56:18,585 --> 00:56:19,836
Yeah. Of course.

670
00:56:20,587 --> 00:56:21,421
Of course.

671
00:56:21,588 --> 00:56:23,308
I think he might be
in some kind of trouble.

672
00:56:23,673 --> 00:56:24,966
Real trouble.

673
00:56:26,634 --> 00:56:28,094
Isn't he always?

674
00:57:02,545 --> 00:57:04,130
Some of you spoke to the police...

675
00:57:04,881 --> 00:57:08,426
about what you believe
you witnessed here yesterday.

676
00:57:11,137 --> 00:57:12,805
You want to know my powers...

677
00:57:14,557 --> 00:57:16,059
know who I am...

678
00:57:17,810 --> 00:57:19,646
see what I can do?

679
00:57:21,898 --> 00:57:23,358
I'll show you.

680
00:57:26,069 --> 00:57:29,030
Think of the person you love most
in your life.

681
00:57:31,407 --> 00:57:32,659
Your wife.

682
00:57:35,495 --> 00:57:36,746
Mother.

683
00:57:39,874 --> 00:57:41,334
Daughter.

684
00:57:45,922 --> 00:57:49,300
Now that person will know what it is
to lose someone they love.

685
00:57:50,301 --> 00:57:52,845
And live with that pain.

686
00:57:54,097 --> 00:57:55,098
Forever.

687
00:57:55,181 --> 00:57:56,724
Henryk, please.

688
00:57:56,933 --> 00:57:58,059
Don't do this.

689
00:57:59,519 --> 00:58:01,229
My name isn't Henryk.

690
00:58:05,316 --> 00:58:07,944
My name is Magneto.

691
00:58:28,423 --> 00:58:29,924
Who the fuck are you?

692
00:58:32,719 --> 00:58:34,429
Stay back.

693
00:58:36,264 --> 00:58:37,265
Whoever you are...

694
00:58:38,391 --> 00:58:40,560
don't try to stop me
from killing these men.

695
00:59:00,038 --> 00:59:01,789
I'm not here for them.

696
00:59:03,791 --> 00:59:05,334
I'm here for you.

697
00:59:22,602 --> 00:59:24,270
Come and see.

698
00:59:57,553 --> 01:00:00,181
This is where your power was born.

699
01:00:02,725 --> 01:00:05,144
And this is where
your people were slaughtered.

700
01:00:20,743 --> 01:00:22,870
You shouldn't have brought me here.

701
01:00:25,289 --> 01:00:26,415
Why?

702
01:00:28,751 --> 01:00:30,878
Are you afraid to be here?

703
01:00:32,505 --> 01:00:35,299
You can't escape it, Erik.

704
01:00:37,426 --> 01:00:39,053
Who are you?

705
01:00:39,220 --> 01:00:42,431
Elohim, Shen, Ra.

706
01:00:42,598 --> 01:00:46,477
I've been called many names
over many lifetimes.

707
01:00:47,645 --> 01:00:50,106
I am born of death.

708
01:00:50,523 --> 01:00:51,983
I was there to spark...

709
01:00:52,150 --> 01:00:55,111
and fan the flame of man's awakening.

710
01:00:55,278 --> 01:00:57,697
To spin the wheel of civilization.

711
01:00:57,864 --> 01:00:59,448
And when the forest would grow rank...

712
01:00:59,615 --> 01:01:01,784
and needed clearing for new growth...

713
01:01:02,827 --> 01:01:06,164
I was there to set it ablaze.

714
01:01:07,582 --> 01:01:09,083
Where were you...

715
01:01:09,250 --> 01:01:11,711
when my father and mother
were slaughtered in this place?

716
01:01:11,878 --> 01:01:12,879
Asleep.

717
01:01:13,462 --> 01:01:15,673
Trapped in darkness.

718
01:01:16,174 --> 01:01:18,134
I was not there for you, my son.

719
01:01:18,301 --> 01:01:20,553
But I am here now.

720
01:01:20,720 --> 01:01:24,390
You don't know your own strength,
but I do.

721
01:01:27,435 --> 01:01:29,228
Reach down.

722
01:01:29,687 --> 01:01:31,105
Feel the metal...

723
01:01:31,272 --> 01:01:33,107
in the ground.

724
01:01:33,274 --> 01:01:36,277
Reach as deep as you can.

725
01:01:39,280 --> 01:01:41,532
You'll find you have the power...

726
01:01:41,699 --> 01:01:44,577
to move the very Earth itself.

727
01:02:17,610 --> 01:02:21,739
Everything they've built will fall!

728
01:02:23,950 --> 01:02:26,619
And from the ashes of their world...

729
01:02:27,954 --> 01:02:31,457
we'll build a better one!

730
01:02:57,984 --> 01:03:01,821
Lehnsherr was identified yesterday,
in this small town in central Poland.

731
01:03:02,405 --> 01:03:06,325
<i>Leaders from all communities are urging
their citizens to remain calm.</i>

732
01:03:06,492 --> 01:03:09,829
{\an8}<i>As police and armed forces
are mobilizing to find Lehnsherr...</i>

733
01:03:09,912 --> 01:03:11,247
{\an8}<i>...before he can strike again.</i>

734
01:03:11,414 --> 01:03:14,500
<i>If anyone has information
about Lehnsherr...</i>

735
01:03:14,667 --> 01:03:16,627
<i>or as he is also known, Magneto...</i>

736
01:03:16,794 --> 01:03:19,297
<i>contact your local authorities
immediately...</i>

737
01:03:19,463 --> 01:03:21,382
<i>and proceed with caution...</i>

738
01:03:21,549 --> 01:03:23,968
<i>- as he is considered extremely...</i>
- Peter.

739
01:03:24,635 --> 01:03:25,636
What's up?

740
01:03:29,140 --> 01:03:30,308
Just checking on you.

741
01:03:30,474 --> 01:03:32,059
I'm good. Playing Pac-Man.

742
01:03:38,107 --> 01:03:39,507
You sure you weren't watching this?

743
01:03:39,567 --> 01:03:41,586
<i>This news comes at a time when the world
is celebrating 10 years of peace...</i>

744
01:03:41,610 --> 01:03:43,696
<i>between mutants and mankind.</i>

745
01:03:43,863 --> 01:03:45,614
You're going after him, aren't you?

746
01:03:47,325 --> 01:03:49,410
You wanted me
to get out of the house more, right?

747
01:03:50,244 --> 01:03:52,955
I can't stop you. Nobody can.

748
01:03:53,122 --> 01:03:55,124
But trust me, this won't end well.

749
01:03:56,292 --> 01:03:57,877
Nothing does with him.

750
01:04:01,714 --> 01:04:03,090
I'm not afraid of him.

751
01:04:03,466 --> 01:04:05,384
You should be.

752
01:04:31,327 --> 01:04:33,412
I've read so much about this place.

753
01:04:34,830 --> 01:04:37,124
But being here,
it actually seems kind of...

754
01:04:37,792 --> 01:04:39,377
familiar.

755
01:04:39,543 --> 01:04:40,544
Strange.

756
01:04:40,711 --> 01:04:41,837
Quite.

757
01:04:42,004 --> 01:04:43,130
Shall we?

758
01:04:45,049 --> 01:04:46,842
I'm just saying, <i>Empire</i> is still the best.

759
01:04:47,009 --> 01:04:49,553
It's the most complex,
the most sophisticated...

760
01:04:49,720 --> 01:04:51,160
wasn't afraid to have a dark ending.

761
01:04:51,222 --> 01:04:52,866
Yeah, but come on.
If it wasn't for the first one...

762
01:04:52,890 --> 01:04:54,534
you wouldn't have any of the rest
of the movies.

763
01:04:54,558 --> 01:04:58,062
Well, at least we can all agree,
the third one's always the worst.

764
01:04:58,854 --> 01:05:00,481
Hank. Are you in here?

765
01:05:00,648 --> 01:05:02,233
I'd like you to meet...

766
01:05:04,276 --> 01:05:05,403
Moira.

767
01:05:05,569 --> 01:05:07,071
Raven.

768
01:05:07,279 --> 01:05:08,906
I'm sorry, have we met?

769
01:05:10,866 --> 01:05:13,452
Hank, Alex, Agent MacTaggert...

770
01:05:13,619 --> 01:05:15,299
would you give us just one moment, please?

771
01:05:16,414 --> 01:05:17,248
Of course.

772
01:05:21,293 --> 01:05:23,773
Charles, why didn't she recognize me?
She knew me in this form.

773
01:05:23,921 --> 01:05:26,632
Well, after you
left me on the beach in Cuba...

774
01:05:26,799 --> 01:05:29,468
I took her memories of that time.
Have a seat.

775
01:05:30,344 --> 01:05:32,012
Lucky girl.

776
01:05:35,015 --> 01:05:36,684
It's good to see you, Raven.

777
01:05:37,017 --> 01:05:39,145
- Welcome home.
- This isn't my home.

778
01:05:40,688 --> 01:05:41,772
It was once.

779
01:05:41,939 --> 01:05:43,774
No, it was your home.
I just lived here.

780
01:05:44,483 --> 01:05:46,277
And I barely even recognize it now.

781
01:05:46,444 --> 01:05:48,237
You know, I have plans for this place.

782
01:05:49,488 --> 01:05:51,198
I mean to turn it into a real campus.

783
01:05:51,365 --> 01:05:52,450
A university.

784
01:05:52,616 --> 01:05:55,453
Not just for mutants, either,
for humans too.

785
01:05:56,370 --> 01:05:57,997
Living and working...

786
01:05:58,747 --> 01:06:00,708
growing together.

787
01:06:01,167 --> 01:06:02,877
You know, I really believed that once.

788
01:06:03,043 --> 01:06:05,838
I really believed we could change them
after DC.

789
01:06:06,380 --> 01:06:07,381
We did.

790
01:06:07,548 --> 01:06:09,508
No, Charles.
They still hate and fear us.

791
01:06:09,675 --> 01:06:12,070
It's just harder to see
because they're more polite about it.

792
01:06:12,094 --> 01:06:13,345
I got sick of living that lie.

793
01:06:13,512 --> 01:06:16,557
That's why you're not in your
natural blue form.

794
01:06:16,724 --> 01:06:19,768
I'm not gonna be the face of a world
that doesn't exist.

795
01:06:20,519 --> 01:06:22,563
Things are better.
The world is better.

796
01:06:22,730 --> 01:06:24,273
Maybe in Westchester.

797
01:06:25,191 --> 01:06:27,067
Out there, mutants are still running...

798
01:06:27,776 --> 01:06:29,361
hiding, living in fear.

799
01:06:29,528 --> 01:06:32,323
Just because there's not a war,
doesn't mean there's peace.

800
01:06:33,032 --> 01:06:34,843
You want to teach your kids something,
teach them that.

801
01:06:34,867 --> 01:06:36,410
Teach them to fight.

802
01:06:36,577 --> 01:06:38,680
Otherwise they might as well live
in this house for the rest of their lives.

803
01:06:38,704 --> 01:06:40,873
You still sound just like him.

804
01:06:41,040 --> 01:06:42,708
You sound just like Erik.

805
01:06:44,960 --> 01:06:46,420
That's why I'm here.

806
01:06:47,254 --> 01:06:48,714
He's resurfaced.

807
01:06:51,217 --> 01:06:53,177
He had a wife and a child.

808
01:06:53,344 --> 01:06:54,553
They were killed.

809
01:06:55,346 --> 01:06:57,389
Along with a handful of policemen.

810
01:06:59,975 --> 01:07:02,603
The whole world will be looking for him.

811
01:07:02,770 --> 01:07:05,314
But you can help me find him
before they do.

812
01:07:13,948 --> 01:07:16,825
Moira, I'm going to have to ask you
to keep this a secret.

813
01:07:16,992 --> 01:07:20,037
I don't even know what this is.

814
01:07:20,204 --> 01:07:21,664
It's Cerebro.

815
01:07:21,830 --> 01:07:22,831
The new model.

816
01:07:22,998 --> 01:07:24,667
I based the color on...

817
01:07:26,961 --> 01:07:27,962
It doesn't matter.

818
01:07:45,896 --> 01:07:47,439
What are those?

819
01:07:47,606 --> 01:07:49,775
Those are all the humans of the world.

820
01:07:51,986 --> 01:07:53,946
And these...

821
01:07:54,363 --> 01:07:56,490
are all the mutants.

822
01:07:56,657 --> 01:07:58,158
I'm connected to all of their minds.

823
01:08:00,202 --> 01:08:02,121
The CIA would kill for this.

824
01:08:02,288 --> 01:08:03,914
I know they would.

825
01:08:06,542 --> 01:08:08,586
Where are you, Erik?

826
01:08:40,534 --> 01:08:41,535
Charles?

827
01:08:43,162 --> 01:08:44,079
Hello, old friend.

828
01:08:46,957 --> 01:08:49,209
I'm sorry. I am so sorry!

829
01:08:49,376 --> 01:08:51,045
I feel your pain.

830
01:08:52,755 --> 01:08:54,340
And your loss.

831
01:08:55,716 --> 01:08:58,344
You think because you can
see into my head...

832
01:08:59,094 --> 01:09:01,096
you know how it feels?

833
01:09:01,930 --> 01:09:04,224
<i>You're looking in the wrong place,
Charles.</i>

834
01:09:04,516 --> 01:09:07,061
What happened to them,
it was terribly wrong.

835
01:09:08,979 --> 01:09:10,230
But come back to us.

836
01:09:10,397 --> 01:09:11,940
<i>I can help you.</i>

837
01:09:12,775 --> 01:09:14,485
Help me?

838
01:09:15,444 --> 01:09:16,921
Think of your wife,
think of your daughter.

839
01:09:16,945 --> 01:09:18,572
<i>What would they have wanted?</i>

840
01:09:18,739 --> 01:09:20,366
They would have wanted to live.

841
01:09:21,283 --> 01:09:23,494
<i>I tried your way, Charles.</i>

842
01:09:24,495 --> 01:09:27,039
<i>I tried to be like them.</i>

843
01:09:27,956 --> 01:09:29,792
Live like them.

844
01:09:32,086 --> 01:09:34,421
But it always ends the same way.

845
01:09:36,340 --> 01:09:38,759
They took everything away from me.

846
01:09:42,721 --> 01:09:43,889
Now...

847
01:09:47,518 --> 01:09:49,520
we'll take everything from them.

848
01:09:58,153 --> 01:09:59,154
Hank...

849
01:10:01,699 --> 01:10:03,450
he's not alone.

850
01:10:10,958 --> 01:10:12,376
Extraordinary.

851
01:10:14,044 --> 01:10:15,587
What do you see?

852
01:10:18,340 --> 01:10:20,092
The answer.

853
01:10:22,636 --> 01:10:23,929
Hey, Charles, wait.

854
01:10:37,317 --> 01:10:38,694
Oh, my God.

855
01:10:39,194 --> 01:10:42,448
Thank you for letting me in.

856
01:10:47,786 --> 01:10:49,121
Charles, get out!

857
01:10:50,956 --> 01:10:54,126
I've never felt power like this before.

858
01:10:54,293 --> 01:10:55,126
Charles...

859
01:10:55,169 --> 01:10:56,420
Charles, get out of there.

860
01:10:56,587 --> 01:10:58,172
What's going on? What's happening?

861
01:10:58,338 --> 01:10:59,173
I think...

862
01:11:00,174 --> 01:11:01,341
Someone's taken over Cerebro.

863
01:11:01,508 --> 01:11:03,427
- They've taken control of it.
- To do what?

864
01:11:05,262 --> 01:11:06,513
To connect.

865
01:11:15,814 --> 01:11:17,608
Always the same.

866
01:11:19,026 --> 01:11:21,695
<i>And now, all this.</i>

867
01:11:25,365 --> 01:11:27,326
<i>No more stones.</i>

868
01:11:30,621 --> 01:11:32,790
<i>No more spears.</i>

869
01:11:39,963 --> 01:11:41,882
<i>No more slings.</i>

870
01:11:46,845 --> 01:11:49,890
<i>No more swords.</i>

871
01:11:50,057 --> 01:11:52,893
No more weapons!

872
01:11:53,519 --> 01:11:56,563
<i>No more systems!</i>

873
01:11:57,397 --> 01:11:59,900
<i>No more!</i>

874
01:12:00,567 --> 01:12:03,403
No more superpowers.

875
01:12:04,822 --> 01:12:05,989
<i>Charles!</i>

876
01:12:09,159 --> 01:12:10,244
Hank!

877
01:12:28,095 --> 01:12:29,555
What the hell is going on?

878
01:12:30,430 --> 01:12:32,015
Who's turning the keys?

879
01:12:32,766 --> 01:12:33,934
The men are.

880
01:12:34,393 --> 01:12:35,686
Who green-lit the launch?

881
01:12:36,186 --> 01:12:38,105
Hank, do something!

882
01:12:42,776 --> 01:12:44,027
It won't shut down!

883
01:12:46,905 --> 01:12:49,408
We've lost contact
with all Trident and Polaris subs.

884
01:12:49,783 --> 01:12:51,743
The Air Force is reporting the same thing.

885
01:12:51,910 --> 01:12:55,205
So much faith in their tools...

886
01:12:55,372 --> 01:12:58,041
and their machines.

887
01:12:58,208 --> 01:12:59,543
<i>Russia, China...</i>

888
01:12:59,710 --> 01:13:02,421
England, Israel, India.

889
01:13:02,588 --> 01:13:04,464
Everybody's got nukes in the air.

890
01:13:04,631 --> 01:13:05,632
What's the target?

891
01:13:05,799 --> 01:13:06,884
Where are they going?

892
01:13:07,050 --> 01:13:08,927
Up, straight up.

893
01:13:09,094 --> 01:13:09,927
Alex...

894
01:13:09,970 --> 01:13:11,263
- What?
- Destroy it!

895
01:13:11,430 --> 01:13:13,390
Destroy everything. Destroy Cerebro!

896
01:13:18,270 --> 01:13:19,396
Wreak havoc!

897
01:13:23,984 --> 01:13:26,653
You can fire your arrows...

898
01:13:26,820 --> 01:13:29,406
<i>from the Tower of Babel...</i>

899
01:13:38,123 --> 01:13:42,502
but you can never strike God!

900
01:14:00,187 --> 01:14:02,272
Charles, are you okay?

901
01:14:20,123 --> 01:14:21,291
Erik.

902
01:14:24,836 --> 01:14:25,837
Charles!

903
01:14:27,339 --> 01:14:28,215
Alex!

904
01:14:29,132 --> 01:14:30,050
Hey!

905
01:14:30,217 --> 01:14:31,050
Hey, asshole!

906
01:14:31,134 --> 01:14:33,303
All will be revealed, my child.

907
01:14:33,470 --> 01:14:34,303
Stop!

908
01:14:34,721 --> 01:14:35,554
No!

909
01:17:31,731 --> 01:17:32,732
Wow!

910
01:17:38,238 --> 01:17:39,739
Where did you...

911
01:17:39,906 --> 01:17:42,534
I was looking for the Professor.
I thought he lived here.

912
01:17:46,037 --> 01:17:47,080
They took him.

913
01:17:48,415 --> 01:17:50,125
She's the one. It's her.

914
01:17:51,126 --> 01:17:52,252
Are you sure?

915
01:17:53,461 --> 01:17:54,462
Is she gonna help us?

916
01:18:04,097 --> 01:18:05,599
They look up to you.

917
01:18:09,686 --> 01:18:10,520
Right now...

918
01:18:11,521 --> 01:18:12,606
they need you.

919
01:18:16,443 --> 01:18:18,111
That's not what they need.

920
01:18:20,280 --> 01:18:21,531
That's awesome!

921
01:18:29,789 --> 01:18:30,790
What happened?

922
01:18:30,957 --> 01:18:32,042
Where's Alex?

923
01:18:32,292 --> 01:18:33,293
Where's my brother?

924
01:18:34,211 --> 01:18:35,587
Pretty sure I got everybody.

925
01:18:38,423 --> 01:18:40,800
Alex was closest to the blast.

926
01:18:56,816 --> 01:18:57,817
Alex...

927
01:19:19,839 --> 01:19:21,007
<i>We're one click out.</i>

928
01:19:22,175 --> 01:19:23,760
<i>All right, boys. This is it.</i>

929
01:19:27,180 --> 01:19:28,181
Scott.

930
01:19:28,348 --> 01:19:31,851
<i>Medical assistance is on the way.</i>

931
01:19:32,852 --> 01:19:35,105
<i>Please remain calm.</i>

932
01:19:35,272 --> 01:19:38,358
<i>Medical assistance is on the way.</i>

933
01:19:39,109 --> 01:19:41,361
<i>Please remain calm.</i>

934
01:19:41,528 --> 01:19:44,698
<i>Medical assistance is on the way.</i>

935
01:19:45,782 --> 01:19:47,200
<i>Please remain calm.</i>

936
01:19:48,451 --> 01:19:50,036
<i>Medical assistance is on the way.</i>

937
01:19:53,164 --> 01:19:55,125
Hey! Moira MacTaggert!

938
01:19:55,292 --> 01:19:56,876
CIA! Thank God you're here!

939
01:20:03,008 --> 01:20:03,883
Wait!

940
01:20:04,676 --> 01:20:05,509
Fire!

941
01:20:11,558 --> 01:20:12,559
I want her.

942
01:20:14,728 --> 01:20:15,562
Him.

943
01:20:17,397 --> 01:20:18,523
Him.

944
01:20:25,572 --> 01:20:27,907
- And her.
- Yes, sir.

945
01:20:31,870 --> 01:20:32,871
Leave the kids.

946
01:20:40,086 --> 01:20:41,504
- What do we do?
- Keep quiet.

947
01:20:43,256 --> 01:20:45,383
X-Ray 7, I'm doing a final sweep
of the ground.

948
01:20:54,017 --> 01:20:56,019
Let's get them on the bird!

949
01:20:56,186 --> 01:20:57,187
Clear!

950
01:21:03,193 --> 01:21:06,112
Thanks, Jean.
We gotta help them.

951
01:21:06,279 --> 01:21:08,839
- Kurt, can you get us in that thing?
- You want to get in there?

952
01:21:09,074 --> 01:21:10,200
What if the soldiers see us?

953
01:21:10,367 --> 01:21:12,035
Don't worry, they won't see us.
Trust me.

954
01:21:14,412 --> 01:21:15,246
Hold on.

955
01:21:31,471 --> 01:21:33,473
Kurt, get us all out of here!

956
01:21:35,141 --> 01:21:36,476
I can't!

957
01:21:36,643 --> 01:21:40,146
When they closed the doors,
there's some kind of electrical field.

958
01:21:40,313 --> 01:21:41,564
It's like Berlin all over.

959
01:21:41,773 --> 01:21:43,417
Jean, get in the pilots' heads.
Don't let them take off.

960
01:21:43,441 --> 01:21:46,611
I can't. I can't reach the pilots.
I can't reach anyone.

961
01:21:54,160 --> 01:21:56,496
<i>We're also getting reports
out of Europe and Asia.</i>

962
01:21:56,663 --> 01:21:58,832
<i>This was not just a U. S. phenomenon.</i>

963
01:21:58,998 --> 01:22:03,169
<i>It seems the entire world
has been disarmed of nuclear weapons.</i>

964
01:22:03,336 --> 01:22:04,814
<i>The Pentagon has confirmed
multiple launches...</i>

965
01:22:04,838 --> 01:22:07,173
<i>from Russia, as well as
the UK, Israel and China.</i>

966
01:22:07,340 --> 01:22:08,675
- Look!
- Look up there!

967
01:22:08,842 --> 01:22:11,344
<i>So far, there has been no response
from the White House.</i>

968
01:22:11,511 --> 01:22:14,514
<i>Eyewitness reports have been pouring in
from affiliates across the globe.</i>

969
01:22:14,681 --> 01:22:18,351
{\an8}<i>Authorities are not sure if it was
an act of peace or an act of war.</i>

970
01:22:25,316 --> 01:22:27,193
Our dear Father...

971
01:22:28,194 --> 01:22:29,779
hold me in the light of God.

972
01:22:34,534 --> 01:22:36,369
It should have been me.

973
01:22:37,787 --> 01:22:40,999
He was the one that was
gonna do something with his life.

974
01:22:41,207 --> 01:22:42,709
He was always the one.

975
01:22:44,461 --> 01:22:46,171
That's not how he felt.

976
01:22:47,005 --> 01:22:50,717
He felt you were the one that was gonna
do something special with your life.

977
01:22:51,885 --> 01:22:54,971
That you were gonna
make a difference in the world.

978
01:22:56,139 --> 01:22:58,349
Maybe even change it.

979
01:22:58,892 --> 01:23:01,060
How do you know what he felt?

980
01:23:02,145 --> 01:23:04,397
I know what everybody feels.

981
01:23:19,913 --> 01:23:22,457
Hold me in the light of God.

982
01:23:23,208 --> 01:23:25,710
Protect me from danger.

983
01:23:26,461 --> 01:23:28,880
<i>Save me by Your command.</i>

984
01:23:30,215 --> 01:23:32,091
<i>Listen to my prayer.</i>

985
01:23:33,176 --> 01:23:35,011
<i>And keep me safe.</i>

986
01:24:10,255 --> 01:24:12,549
You're blocking me.

987
01:24:12,715 --> 01:24:13,716
How?

988
01:24:13,883 --> 01:24:16,177
I can shield their minds from your power.

989
01:24:16,344 --> 01:24:19,806
It's one of the many gifts I've acquired
throughout the millennia.

990
01:24:19,973 --> 01:24:22,600
But to see...

991
01:24:22,767 --> 01:24:24,310
inside a mind...

992
01:24:24,477 --> 01:24:26,688
to control it...

993
01:24:27,939 --> 01:24:29,482
that's your gift.

994
01:24:31,067 --> 01:24:33,194
You saw it, didn't you?

995
01:24:33,361 --> 01:24:35,446
The glory of what's to come.

996
01:24:36,447 --> 01:24:38,327
You're going to take part
in all this killing...

997
01:24:39,659 --> 01:24:41,703
and destruction?

998
01:24:42,245 --> 01:24:43,496
It's all I've ever known.

999
01:24:43,663 --> 01:24:45,331
No, it isn't.

1000
01:24:45,707 --> 01:24:46,833
You've just forgotten.

1001
01:24:47,000 --> 01:24:48,918
No, Charles, I remember.

1002
01:24:51,254 --> 01:24:52,797
Your way doesn't work.

1003
01:24:53,172 --> 01:24:55,967
I've shown him a better way.

1004
01:24:56,134 --> 01:24:57,427
A better world.

1005
01:24:57,594 --> 01:25:00,680
No, you've just tapped into his rage
and pain. That's all you've done.

1006
01:25:01,264 --> 01:25:04,559
I told you from the moment I met you,
there is more to you, Erik.

1007
01:25:04,726 --> 01:25:07,353
There is good in you, too.

1008
01:25:07,520 --> 01:25:10,315
Whatever it is you think
you saw in me, Charles...

1009
01:25:12,650 --> 01:25:14,319
I buried it...

1010
01:25:14,485 --> 01:25:17,280
with my family.

1011
01:25:28,958 --> 01:25:29,791
What?

1012
01:25:30,418 --> 01:25:31,794
What's wrong with you?

1013
01:25:31,961 --> 01:25:33,880
Is that going to happen to all of us?

1014
01:25:34,881 --> 01:25:35,798
No, I just...

1015
01:25:35,965 --> 01:25:37,216
left my meds in the house.

1016
01:25:38,176 --> 01:25:39,302
What happened? Where are we?

1017
01:25:39,469 --> 01:25:40,303
Hey!

1018
01:25:41,012 --> 01:25:42,013
<i>Hello, Mystique.</i>

1019
01:25:42,263 --> 01:25:43,598
<i>Major Stryker.</i>

1020
01:25:43,765 --> 01:25:44,682
Colonel Stryker.

1021
01:25:44,849 --> 01:25:46,976
I wouldn't get too close to the wall,
if I were you.

1022
01:25:47,143 --> 01:25:49,228
<i>It may create some discomfort.</i>

1023
01:25:49,395 --> 01:25:51,981
I'm Moira MacTaggert.
I'm a senior officer at the CIA.

1024
01:25:52,148 --> 01:25:54,275
<i>I know who you are, Agent MacTaggert.</i>

1025
01:25:54,442 --> 01:25:56,152
You cannot keep me here, in this...

1026
01:25:56,319 --> 01:25:57,528
Actually, I can.

1027
01:25:57,695 --> 01:26:01,616
<i>A psychic event just destroyed
every nuke from here to Moscow.</i>

1028
01:26:01,783 --> 01:26:05,495
<i>That event emanated from exactly
where we found you.</i>

1029
01:26:05,662 --> 01:26:08,122
<i>At the home of the world's
most powerful psychic.</i>

1030
01:26:08,289 --> 01:26:11,209
So, you are going to tell me,
where is Charles Xavier?

1031
01:26:12,752 --> 01:26:14,392
It's not him you should be worried about.

1032
01:26:14,545 --> 01:26:17,632
There's someone else.
Someone more powerful.

1033
01:26:18,299 --> 01:26:21,386
<i>If you let us out of here,
we can help you.</i>

1034
01:26:22,470 --> 01:26:25,056
Do you really expect me to believe that?

1035
01:26:25,598 --> 01:26:28,267
<i>You can put on any face that you want,
but I know who you are.</i>

1036
01:26:28,434 --> 01:26:29,811
<i>What you are.</i>

1037
01:26:35,233 --> 01:26:36,859
Hey, Moira.

1038
01:26:37,026 --> 01:26:38,778
What did you mean when you said...

1039
01:26:38,945 --> 01:26:40,822
someone more powerful than Charles?

1040
01:26:43,074 --> 01:26:44,794
Once they finish these,
we'll go from there.

1041
01:26:51,499 --> 01:26:52,917
What's taking so long?

1042
01:26:53,084 --> 01:26:54,210
I can't get in.

1043
01:26:54,377 --> 01:26:57,046
They have a field around it,
like the helicopter.

1044
01:26:57,255 --> 01:26:59,298
There's gotta be a way to cut the power.

1045
01:26:59,465 --> 01:27:00,466
<i>Charles...</i>

1046
01:27:00,842 --> 01:27:02,927
you will send a message...

1047
01:27:03,094 --> 01:27:04,762
to every living mind.

1048
01:27:04,929 --> 01:27:08,683
You will tell them
that this earth will be laid waste.

1049
01:27:08,850 --> 01:27:10,601
That it is I, En Sabah Nur...

1050
01:27:10,768 --> 01:27:12,478
who will wreak this upon them.

1051
01:27:19,152 --> 01:27:20,778
Now...

1052
01:27:20,945 --> 01:27:23,948
deliver my message.

1053
01:27:24,115 --> 01:27:25,908
Even if I wanted to...

1054
01:27:26,075 --> 01:27:28,578
I couldn't reach that many people.
I don't have Cerebro.

1055
01:27:32,123 --> 01:27:33,583
You don't need a machine...

1056
01:27:33,750 --> 01:27:36,169
to amplify your powers.

1057
01:27:37,044 --> 01:27:39,088
You have me.

1058
01:27:52,143 --> 01:27:54,771
Guys, that could be our way out of here.

1059
01:27:59,150 --> 01:28:00,985
You know him? Magneto?

1060
01:28:02,570 --> 01:28:03,905
I used to.

1061
01:28:04,822 --> 01:28:06,115
Not so sure anymore.

1062
01:28:06,616 --> 01:28:08,326
What was he like?

1063
01:28:08,493 --> 01:28:11,496
Was he like they say he was?
Was he...

1064
01:28:13,164 --> 01:28:14,373
the bad guy?

1065
01:28:14,540 --> 01:28:15,625
No.

1066
01:28:16,751 --> 01:28:19,712
I mean, yeah. He was...

1067
01:28:21,839 --> 01:28:24,550
Why do you care so much?
You see his speech on TV or something?

1068
01:28:25,009 --> 01:28:27,386
Yeah, but...

1069
01:28:31,557 --> 01:28:33,059
He's my father.

1070
01:28:33,226 --> 01:28:34,352
What?

1071
01:28:34,727 --> 01:28:36,487
- Him and my mom, they did it.
- No, I know--

1072
01:28:36,938 --> 01:28:38,064
Are you sure?

1073
01:28:38,231 --> 01:28:41,108
Yeah. He left my mom before I was born.

1074
01:28:41,526 --> 01:28:42,693
I met him 10 years back...

1075
01:28:42,860 --> 01:28:44,320
but I didn't know it was him.

1076
01:28:44,487 --> 01:28:47,114
By the time I figured it out,
it was too late.

1077
01:28:47,573 --> 01:28:49,617
Then, this week I saw him on TV again...

1078
01:28:49,784 --> 01:28:52,286
and I came to that house,
looking for him...

1079
01:28:52,453 --> 01:28:54,664
but by the time I got there...

1080
01:28:56,958 --> 01:28:58,251
Late again.

1081
01:29:00,837 --> 01:29:02,588
For a guy who moves as fast as me...

1082
01:29:02,755 --> 01:29:04,966
I always seem to be too late.

1083
01:29:05,842 --> 01:29:07,802
Let's hope not this time.

1084
01:29:08,886 --> 01:29:09,720
Yeah.

1085
01:29:09,887 --> 01:29:10,930
Seriously.

1086
01:29:11,097 --> 01:29:12,056
<i>Hear me...</i>

1087
01:29:12,223 --> 01:29:13,891
<i>inhabitants of this world.</i>

1088
01:29:15,268 --> 01:29:16,894
- What is that?
<i>- This is a message.</i>

1089
01:29:17,061 --> 01:29:18,604
I think it's the Professor.

1090
01:29:18,771 --> 01:29:22,608
<i>A message to every man, woman,
and mutant in the world.</i>

1091
01:29:22,775 --> 01:29:25,611
You have lost your way.

1092
01:29:26,529 --> 01:29:28,573
You have lost your way.

1093
01:29:28,739 --> 01:29:30,157
But I have returned.

1094
01:29:31,242 --> 01:29:33,870
But I have returned.

1095
01:29:34,745 --> 01:29:37,331
<i>The day of reckoning is here.</i>

1096
01:29:38,708 --> 01:29:40,418
<i>All your buildings...</i>

1097
01:29:40,501 --> 01:29:44,589
...all of your towers and temples...

1098
01:29:45,047 --> 01:29:46,632
Will fall.

1099
01:29:46,966 --> 01:29:52,471
And the dawn of a new age will rise.

1100
01:29:52,805 --> 01:29:54,325
<i>...for there is nothing you can do...</i>

1101
01:29:55,057 --> 01:29:56,642
<i>- Jean.
- ...to stop what is coming.</i>

1102
01:29:58,019 --> 01:30:01,397
<i>Jean, if you can hear me,
focus on my voice.</i>

1103
01:30:01,564 --> 01:30:03,941
<i>Cairo.
Find us, Jean.</i>

1104
01:30:04,108 --> 01:30:05,526
<i>Find us. Cairo. Find us.</i>

1105
01:30:06,527 --> 01:30:09,447
<i>This message is for one reason alone.</i>

1106
01:30:09,614 --> 01:30:11,824
To tell the strongest among you...

1107
01:30:11,991 --> 01:30:15,953
Those with the greatest power...

1108
01:30:16,120 --> 01:30:19,540
this earth will be yours.

1109
01:30:20,374 --> 01:30:22,543
Those with the greatest power...

1110
01:30:25,546 --> 01:30:27,214
protect those without.

1111
01:30:30,426 --> 01:30:33,137
That's my message to the world.

1112
01:30:37,433 --> 01:30:39,352
How was Charles doing that
without Cerebro?

1113
01:30:40,102 --> 01:30:42,021
Sir, what was that voice?

1114
01:30:43,105 --> 01:30:44,231
<i>I know that voice.</i>

1115
01:30:44,357 --> 01:30:45,942
<i>It's Xavier, isn't it?
What's going on?</i>

1116
01:30:46,108 --> 01:30:47,818
- We don't know!
- We don't know, bro!

1117
01:30:48,736 --> 01:30:49,820
He just spoke to me.

1118
01:30:49,987 --> 01:30:52,073
I think he spoke to everyone.

1119
01:30:52,239 --> 01:30:53,658
- I could hear him, too.
- No, no...

1120
01:30:53,824 --> 01:30:55,493
he just sent me a hidden message.

1121
01:30:55,660 --> 01:30:57,161
One he knew only I would hear.

1122
01:30:58,037 --> 01:30:59,080
I know where they are.

1123
01:30:59,830 --> 01:31:00,831
Hey!

1124
01:31:02,249 --> 01:31:04,335
<i>We have shots fired!
Where's it coming from?</i>

1125
01:31:05,836 --> 01:31:07,338
I have intruders in Quad Six.

1126
01:31:09,465 --> 01:31:11,425
Send a security team.
Take them out.

1127
01:31:19,308 --> 01:31:21,394
The generator. It's worth a shot.

1128
01:31:22,311 --> 01:31:23,437
Kurt?

1129
01:31:44,959 --> 01:31:47,461
There's some kind of animal in there.

1130
01:31:50,589 --> 01:31:53,050
It's no animal.

1131
01:31:53,759 --> 01:31:54,760
It's a man.

1132
01:31:55,636 --> 01:31:56,637
Who is he?

1133
01:31:58,055 --> 01:32:00,307
That part of him as been taken away.

1134
01:32:01,350 --> 01:32:02,727
What do you mean?

1135
01:32:02,893 --> 01:32:06,313
I mean they turned him into
some kind of weapon.

1136
01:32:11,652 --> 01:32:14,113
<i>Charlie Three, report.
Did you find them?</i>

1137
01:32:25,791 --> 01:32:26,792
Shut it down.

1138
01:32:50,775 --> 01:32:51,650
Fire!

1139
01:33:02,453 --> 01:33:03,954
Weapon X is loose!

1140
01:33:04,497 --> 01:33:06,916
I repeat, Weapon X is loose!

1141
01:33:09,335 --> 01:33:10,878
You sure he's not an animal?

1142
01:33:15,716 --> 01:33:18,844
- He's into the central halls.
<i>- Engaging target Sector Five.</i>

1143
01:33:19,595 --> 01:33:20,429
<i>We can't...</i>

1144
01:33:36,862 --> 01:33:37,863
Hey!

1145
01:33:58,592 --> 01:34:00,192
- What are they doing?
- What's going on?

1146
01:34:00,302 --> 01:34:02,638
<i>- I just lost feed.
- Hey! What's going on here?</i>

1147
01:34:04,473 --> 01:34:05,641
I'll be right back.

1148
01:34:08,853 --> 01:34:09,895
No!

1149
01:34:26,787 --> 01:34:29,540
Hey! Stay where you are!

1150
01:34:48,809 --> 01:34:49,727
Scott, wait.

1151
01:34:52,438 --> 01:34:53,772
<i>I can help you.</i>

1152
01:34:59,778 --> 01:35:01,030
Jean.

1153
01:35:39,652 --> 01:35:41,612
<i>Logan.</i>

1154
01:36:29,535 --> 01:36:31,036
What'd you do to him?

1155
01:36:32,454 --> 01:36:36,000
I found a piece of his past
and gave it back to him.

1156
01:36:36,333 --> 01:36:38,711
Just the few memories I could reach.

1157
01:36:40,629 --> 01:36:42,965
I hope that's the last we've seen
of that guy.

1158
01:37:02,401 --> 01:37:03,402
Kurt.

1159
01:37:06,196 --> 01:37:07,531
- What?
- What?

1160
01:37:07,698 --> 01:37:08,699
Hey.

1161
01:37:13,746 --> 01:37:16,081
<i>Stay away from the...</i>

1162
01:37:16,248 --> 01:37:17,124
The what?

1163
01:37:17,541 --> 01:37:18,751
<i>The do-...</i>

1164
01:37:18,917 --> 01:37:20,085
<i>Stay away from the...</i>

1165
01:37:20,252 --> 01:37:21,378
Get away from the door!

1166
01:37:21,545 --> 01:37:22,546
<i>On three.</i>

1167
01:37:22,713 --> 01:37:24,923
<i>One... two...</i>

1168
01:37:37,936 --> 01:37:39,438
We know where the Professor is.

1169
01:37:39,605 --> 01:37:41,082
I think we might have a way out of here.

1170
01:37:41,106 --> 01:37:44,026
- Well, you've been busy.
- We had a little help.

1171
01:37:45,110 --> 01:37:45,943
Let's go!

1172
01:37:49,365 --> 01:37:50,366
Jesus!

1173
01:37:50,532 --> 01:37:51,533
Oh, sorry!

1174
01:37:51,700 --> 01:37:52,868
This way!

1175
01:38:02,294 --> 01:38:04,797
This was meant to be
the center of the universe...

1176
01:38:04,963 --> 01:38:06,715
before I was betrayed.

1177
01:38:06,882 --> 01:38:08,467
Now...

1178
01:38:08,634 --> 01:38:09,968
it will be.

1179
01:39:30,716 --> 01:39:31,842
Nice.

1180
01:39:32,634 --> 01:39:35,345
Hey, Hank, do you think
you can fly this thing?

1181
01:39:35,804 --> 01:39:37,639
Yeah, I can figure it out.

1182
01:39:39,016 --> 01:39:39,850
Hey, guys.

1183
01:39:41,310 --> 01:39:42,853
Flight suits.

1184
01:39:46,690 --> 01:39:48,692
You got your warplane.

1185
01:39:48,859 --> 01:39:50,235
Let's go to war.

1186
01:39:57,493 --> 01:39:59,244
A gift...

1187
01:39:59,411 --> 01:40:01,330
from the past you left behind...

1188
01:40:02,539 --> 01:40:05,250
and the future that lies ahead.

1189
01:40:06,668 --> 01:40:10,172
You will reach down, my son.

1190
01:40:10,339 --> 01:40:12,466
Deep into the earth.

1191
01:40:12,633 --> 01:40:15,886
Rip everything they've
built from the ground.

1192
01:40:16,053 --> 01:40:18,639
Wipe clean this world.

1193
01:40:18,805 --> 01:40:22,351
And we will lead those that survive...

1194
01:40:22,518 --> 01:40:25,312
into a better one.

1195
01:40:25,729 --> 01:40:27,272
And me?

1196
01:40:28,440 --> 01:40:31,026
Am I to play a role in this madness?

1197
01:40:32,736 --> 01:40:36,365
You have the most important role of all.

1198
01:40:47,668 --> 01:40:49,378
Were you scared?

1199
01:40:49,878 --> 01:40:51,838
That day in D.C., were you scared?

1200
01:40:52,005 --> 01:40:52,839
No.

1201
01:40:59,221 --> 01:41:01,890
But I was scared on my first mission.

1202
01:41:02,266 --> 01:41:04,309
I was on a plane like this
with my friends.

1203
01:41:04,726 --> 01:41:06,061
About your age.

1204
01:41:09,690 --> 01:41:11,942
We called ourselves the X-Men.

1205
01:41:13,402 --> 01:41:14,903
Your brother was there.

1206
01:41:15,445 --> 01:41:16,822
We used to call him Havok.

1207
01:41:17,364 --> 01:41:19,283
He was a real handful...

1208
01:41:21,243 --> 01:41:23,829
but when it came down to it,
he was very brave.

1209
01:41:26,164 --> 01:41:28,834
What happened to the rest of the kids
who went with you?

1210
01:41:29,001 --> 01:41:30,168
The X-Men?

1211
01:41:32,963 --> 01:41:34,756
Hank and I are the only ones left.

1212
01:41:35,882 --> 01:41:37,718
I couldn't save the rest of them.

1213
01:41:38,719 --> 01:41:40,721
I told you, I'm not a hero.

1214
01:41:41,221 --> 01:41:43,098
Well, you're a hero to us.

1215
01:41:43,807 --> 01:41:45,559
Seeing you that day on TV...

1216
01:41:45,726 --> 01:41:46,977
changed my life.

1217
01:41:47,519 --> 01:41:48,604
Mine, too.

1218
01:41:49,646 --> 01:41:50,647
Mine, too.

1219
01:41:52,524 --> 01:41:56,069
I still live in my mom's basement
but, you know...

1220
01:41:56,236 --> 01:41:57,904
everything else is...

1221
01:41:59,656 --> 01:42:01,575
It's pretty much the same.

1222
01:42:03,452 --> 01:42:04,828
I'm a total loser.

1223
01:43:04,971 --> 01:43:07,265
What we're seeing is
a magnetic phenomenon...

1224
01:43:07,432 --> 01:43:10,018
on a much larger scale
than what we saw at Auschwitz.

1225
01:43:10,310 --> 01:43:12,729
The ground is full of magnetic elements.

1226
01:43:12,896 --> 01:43:14,523
Iron, nickel, cobalt.

1227
01:43:14,690 --> 01:43:17,067
The ocean's floor is lined with them, too.

1228
01:43:17,234 --> 01:43:19,903
It's already begun at the lowest depths.

1229
01:43:20,070 --> 01:43:23,198
Land masses will slow it,
but not for long.

1230
01:43:23,365 --> 01:43:26,201
Eventually, cities, urban centers...

1231
01:43:26,368 --> 01:43:28,620
anything built since the Bronze Age...

1232
01:43:28,787 --> 01:43:30,080
will be wiped away.

1233
01:43:30,247 --> 01:43:31,807
The death toll will be in the billions.

1234
01:43:31,832 --> 01:43:34,209
He's talking about
the whole goddamn world.

1235
01:44:23,550 --> 01:44:24,801
You're just another false god.

1236
01:44:25,844 --> 01:44:28,138
And whoever's left to follow you
when this all over...

1237
01:44:28,305 --> 01:44:31,391
they will betray you again.

1238
01:44:33,602 --> 01:44:35,520
You're wrong, Charles.

1239
01:44:35,937 --> 01:44:39,524
For the first time
in a thousand lifetimes...

1240
01:44:39,691 --> 01:44:41,193
I have you.

1241
01:44:41,693 --> 01:44:47,282
For all my gifts, I have yet
to possess the one I needed most.

1242
01:44:47,949 --> 01:44:49,159
To be...

1243
01:44:49,910 --> 01:44:51,828
everywhere.

1244
01:44:54,873 --> 01:44:56,041
To be...

1245
01:44:56,833 --> 01:44:58,084
everyone.

1246
01:45:13,892 --> 01:45:15,811
Seventh wonder, twelve o' clock.

1247
01:45:24,069 --> 01:45:26,071
He has the Professor
in the center of the pyramid.

1248
01:45:27,239 --> 01:45:30,617
He's going to transfer his consciousness
into the Professor.

1249
01:45:30,784 --> 01:45:31,617
If he does that...

1250
01:45:32,160 --> 01:45:35,121
he'll have the power
to control every mind in the world.

1251
01:45:42,170 --> 01:45:44,339
What the hell is that?

1252
01:45:45,257 --> 01:45:46,424
It's Erik.

1253
01:45:56,351 --> 01:45:58,311
You guys help Nightcrawler
get into the pyramid.

1254
01:46:00,272 --> 01:46:02,816
Get Charles. I'll take care of Erik.

1255
01:46:02,983 --> 01:46:04,776
How are we gonna get through that?

1256
01:46:05,610 --> 01:46:06,778
I can get you in there.

1257
01:46:07,445 --> 01:46:08,989
I came here for him. Let me help you.

1258
01:46:10,365 --> 01:46:13,005
The rest of you, get Charles on this
plane and get him out of here.

1259
01:46:13,118 --> 01:46:14,958
- We're not leaving without you!
- Don't worry.

1260
01:46:15,704 --> 01:46:16,663
We'll catch up.

1261
01:46:16,955 --> 01:46:18,039
Hold on.

1262
01:46:48,653 --> 01:46:49,863
Hank, you go with the kids.

1263
01:46:50,030 --> 01:46:52,324
- Moira will be waiting on the plane.
- Wait.

1264
01:46:52,657 --> 01:46:53,658
What?

1265
01:46:53,825 --> 01:46:56,161
Not all of us can
fully control our powers.

1266
01:46:56,661 --> 01:46:57,996
Then don't.

1267
01:46:58,330 --> 01:46:59,998
You need to embrace them.

1268
01:47:03,335 --> 01:47:04,419
We all do.

1269
01:47:28,443 --> 01:47:31,363
Go. Join the others.

1270
01:47:31,529 --> 01:47:34,699
Protect me,
until the transference is complete.

1271
01:47:59,891 --> 01:48:01,393
There's an entrance. It's clear.

1272
01:48:05,730 --> 01:48:07,315
Kurt! Get in there!

1273
01:48:18,243 --> 01:48:19,577
In the pyramid! Move!

1274
01:48:20,328 --> 01:48:21,329
Go!

1275
01:48:57,824 --> 01:48:58,950
Split them up.

1276
01:49:22,640 --> 01:49:23,641
Professor...

1277
01:49:27,645 --> 01:49:28,813
Kurt, you have to hurry!

1278
01:49:28,980 --> 01:49:31,149
I'm trying. It's like a maze in here.

1279
01:49:41,493 --> 01:49:42,494
Kurt, no!

1280
01:50:08,019 --> 01:50:10,300
The magnetic field is too strong.
I can't get us in there.

1281
01:50:12,857 --> 01:50:13,942
Erik!

1282
01:50:21,199 --> 01:50:22,200
Mystique.

1283
01:50:26,538 --> 01:50:29,457
I know you think you've lost everything.

1284
01:50:30,250 --> 01:50:31,709
But you haven't.

1285
01:50:33,294 --> 01:50:35,380
You have me.

1286
01:50:35,713 --> 01:50:37,465
You have Charles.

1287
01:50:43,555 --> 01:50:46,224
You have more family than you know.

1288
01:50:47,392 --> 01:50:50,061
You never had the chance
to save your family before.

1289
01:50:51,229 --> 01:50:52,897
But you do now.

1290
01:50:55,567 --> 01:50:58,069
That's what I've come here to tell you.

1291
01:51:03,449 --> 01:51:05,076
And you?

1292
01:51:13,918 --> 01:51:15,587
I'm your...

1293
01:51:19,924 --> 01:51:22,260
I'm here for my family, too.

1294
01:52:11,517 --> 01:52:13,353
Get out. Get out!

1295
01:52:13,519 --> 01:52:14,812
Get out!

1296
01:52:21,694 --> 01:52:23,154
<i>Auf Wiedersehen.</i>

1297
01:52:34,749 --> 01:52:36,167
We're losing him.

1298
01:52:52,350 --> 01:52:53,268
I'll be right back.

1299
01:53:04,404 --> 01:53:05,697
Scott, glasses on!

1300
01:53:15,707 --> 01:53:16,541
Let's go!

1301
01:53:33,558 --> 01:53:35,059
- Locked on.
- Here we go.

1302
01:53:52,910 --> 01:53:54,078
Psylocke!

1303
01:54:10,428 --> 01:54:11,637
What the hell was that?

1304
01:54:18,311 --> 01:54:19,437
Kurt.

1305
01:54:19,771 --> 01:54:21,211
Everyone, grab hold of Nightcrawler!

1306
01:54:21,272 --> 01:54:22,750
I've never done it with this many people.

1307
01:54:22,774 --> 01:54:23,608
Get us out of here.

1308
01:54:39,624 --> 01:54:40,792
Kurt, hurry!

1309
01:54:42,377 --> 01:54:43,294
Kurt!

1310
01:55:09,404 --> 01:55:10,905
Charles...

1311
01:55:16,327 --> 01:55:17,161
Is he okay?

1312
01:55:17,829 --> 01:55:20,081
It's his energy. He's drained.

1313
01:55:21,499 --> 01:55:22,500
Get out.

1314
01:55:23,501 --> 01:55:24,335
Get out!

1315
01:55:24,502 --> 01:55:26,838
Professor, it's okay.
You're with us.

1316
01:55:27,922 --> 01:55:29,340
It's okay.

1317
01:55:38,015 --> 01:55:40,643
I'm going to fight for what I have left.

1318
01:55:44,021 --> 01:55:45,982
Are you?

1319
01:55:58,828 --> 01:56:01,330
There's so much more to you than you know.

1320
01:56:01,497 --> 01:56:04,459
Not just pain and anger.

1321
01:56:04,625 --> 01:56:06,502
There's good, too. I felt it.

1322
01:56:07,003 --> 01:56:08,880
It's not just me you're walking away from.

1323
01:56:09,046 --> 01:56:13,217
Here, you have the chance to be a part of
something much bigger than yourself.

1324
01:56:13,384 --> 01:56:16,220
And it needs you, Erik.

1325
01:56:45,041 --> 01:56:47,168
Useless.

1326
01:56:52,507 --> 01:56:53,841
<i>Charles.</i>

1327
01:56:56,093 --> 01:56:58,221
I know you can hear me.

1328
01:56:59,096 --> 01:57:02,099
We're still connected.

1329
01:57:05,895 --> 01:57:06,896
Charles!

1330
01:57:08,022 --> 01:57:09,440
Show yourself!

1331
01:57:11,067 --> 01:57:12,610
Charles!

1332
01:57:13,402 --> 01:57:15,613
Show yourself!

1333
01:57:45,226 --> 01:57:47,103
Foolish child.

1334
01:57:55,778 --> 01:57:56,737
Peter.

1335
01:58:13,838 --> 01:58:14,839
End him.

1336
01:58:41,532 --> 01:58:42,533
Raven.

1337
01:58:50,833 --> 01:58:52,209
The great hero.

1338
01:58:57,298 --> 01:58:59,508
- I'm going out there.
- I'm going with you.

1339
01:58:59,675 --> 01:59:00,885
No.

1340
01:59:02,094 --> 01:59:03,304
It's me he wants.

1341
01:59:03,471 --> 01:59:04,911
Charles, you can't give yourself up.

1342
01:59:05,181 --> 01:59:07,058
If he has you, he has us all.

1343
01:59:07,224 --> 01:59:08,851
The whole world.

1344
01:59:09,018 --> 01:59:10,770
You are feeble.

1345
01:59:10,936 --> 01:59:11,979
Just like the others.

1346
01:59:13,189 --> 01:59:14,190
Charles!

1347
01:59:14,357 --> 01:59:15,191
Come!

1348
01:59:15,358 --> 01:59:16,984
Rescue your weaklings!

1349
01:59:18,361 --> 01:59:20,196
Give your life for theirs!

1350
01:59:22,239 --> 01:59:23,240
No.

1351
01:59:31,374 --> 01:59:32,416
He was right.

1352
01:59:33,542 --> 01:59:36,045
There is still some part of me
connected to him.

1353
01:59:37,004 --> 01:59:37,837
Charles!

1354
01:59:37,963 --> 01:59:39,548
I can get inside his head.

1355
01:59:39,715 --> 01:59:41,634
Will you do nothing?

1356
01:59:43,052 --> 01:59:44,804
Thank you for letting me in.

1357
02:00:02,947 --> 02:00:04,490
You want what I have?

1358
02:00:04,657 --> 02:00:06,826
You want to feel what I feel?

1359
02:00:18,629 --> 02:00:19,964
Welcome to my world!

1360
02:00:22,633 --> 02:00:23,634
You're in my house now!

1361
02:00:34,061 --> 02:00:36,063
You'll need a bigger house.

1362
02:01:55,476 --> 02:01:57,061
You betray me?

1363
02:01:57,228 --> 02:01:58,229
No.

1364
02:01:59,146 --> 02:02:00,648
I betrayed them.

1365
02:02:28,926 --> 02:02:30,010
Let's jump.

1366
02:02:30,177 --> 02:02:31,011
What?

1367
02:02:36,433 --> 02:02:37,434
Cover me.

1368
02:02:39,895 --> 02:02:41,397
I got you.

1369
02:02:46,569 --> 02:02:47,778
Come on!

1370
02:03:09,049 --> 02:03:11,635
They lack strength, Charles.

1371
02:03:17,808 --> 02:03:19,101
Jean.

1372
02:03:24,773 --> 02:03:26,066
Come here.

1373
02:03:38,454 --> 02:03:39,747
Help...

1374
02:03:42,249 --> 02:03:43,584
me.

1375
02:03:48,464 --> 02:03:49,840
Stay here.

1376
02:03:59,141 --> 02:04:00,768
They can't stop him.

1377
02:04:01,435 --> 02:04:02,603
Jean.

1378
02:04:05,022 --> 02:04:07,232
Help me!

1379
02:04:30,297 --> 02:04:31,423
Hank!

1380
02:04:32,675 --> 02:04:33,508
Hank!

1381
02:04:40,933 --> 02:04:43,894
It's over, Charles.
You're finished.

1382
02:04:44,061 --> 02:04:45,646
You're mine now.

1383
02:04:48,065 --> 02:04:50,734
You will never win.

1384
02:04:51,193 --> 02:04:53,112
And why is that?

1385
02:04:53,278 --> 02:04:55,406
Because you are alone.

1386
02:04:57,282 --> 02:05:00,619
And I am not!

1387
02:05:12,673 --> 02:05:13,841
<i>Let...</i>

1388
02:05:14,299 --> 02:05:15,676
go.

1389
02:05:16,301 --> 02:05:18,095
<i>Unleash your power, Jean.</i>

1390
02:05:19,555 --> 02:05:20,848
No fear.

1391
02:06:08,979 --> 02:06:11,190
Unleash your power!

1392
02:06:11,648 --> 02:06:13,358
Let go, Jean!

1393
02:06:13,817 --> 02:06:15,778
Jean, let go!

1394
02:06:51,605 --> 02:06:53,232
He's getting away.

1395
02:07:10,749 --> 02:07:14,378
All is revealed.

1396
02:08:16,190 --> 02:08:17,941
Charles! Charles!

1397
02:08:19,443 --> 02:08:20,523
- We've lost him!
- Charles.

1398
02:08:20,611 --> 02:08:22,279
- He's gone.
- No, Charles.

1399
02:08:22,446 --> 02:08:23,447
Charles...

1400
02:08:23,947 --> 02:08:25,115
No, he's not.

1401
02:08:26,533 --> 02:08:27,784
I can still feel him.

1402
02:08:51,975 --> 02:08:53,644
Thank you, Jean.

1403
02:08:55,729 --> 02:08:56,730
Charles?

1404
02:08:57,731 --> 02:08:59,358
Charles, do you know where you are?

1405
02:09:02,819 --> 02:09:04,488
I'm on a beach.

1406
02:09:10,577 --> 02:09:12,246
In Cuba.

1407
02:09:13,997 --> 02:09:15,415
With you.

1408
02:09:15,832 --> 02:09:17,334
What beach?

1409
02:09:24,883 --> 02:09:25,716
Charles Xavier.

1410
02:09:52,786 --> 02:09:53,870
I'm sorry.

1411
02:09:54,871 --> 02:09:57,207
I should never have taken those from you.

1412
02:10:00,627 --> 02:10:01,753
Hold on!

1413
02:10:06,758 --> 02:10:08,051
What did I miss?

1414
02:10:10,929 --> 02:10:13,390
<i>It seems only by the grace of God...</i>

1415
02:10:13,557 --> 02:10:14,797
<i>that the ominous destruction...</i>

1416
02:10:14,933 --> 02:10:17,769
<i>seen from one end of the globe
to the other, has stopped.</i>

1417
02:10:17,936 --> 02:10:20,314
<i>At a debriefing today,
CIA Special Agent Moira MacTaggert...</i>

1418
02:10:20,480 --> 02:10:22,649
<i>revealed to an investigative committee...</i>

1419
02:10:22,816 --> 02:10:25,777
<i>The committee was further stunned
to learn that fugitive Erik Lehnsherr...</i>

1420
02:10:25,944 --> 02:10:28,155
<i>aided in defeating
this powerful and unknown...</i>

1421
02:10:28,322 --> 02:10:30,657
I think our prayers were answered.

1422
02:10:31,408 --> 02:10:32,826
Thank you, Mr. President.

1423
02:10:32,993 --> 02:10:34,637
<i>The potential destructive power
of mutants...</i>

1424
02:10:34,661 --> 02:10:36,747
<i>...is sure to fuel new controversy
and debate...</i>

1425
02:10:36,913 --> 02:10:40,625
<i>at a time when mutants were becoming
accepted around the world.</i>

1426
02:11:07,778 --> 02:11:10,197
Mystique told me he is your father.

1427
02:11:11,323 --> 02:11:13,367
Are you gonna tell him?

1428
02:11:14,618 --> 02:11:15,619
I might...

1429
02:11:16,536 --> 02:11:17,704
one day.

1430
02:11:19,289 --> 02:11:22,209
I think for now, I'm just gonna
stick around here for a while.

1431
02:11:27,964 --> 02:11:29,132
Me, too.

1432
02:11:40,227 --> 02:11:43,230
The world's already begun
rebuilding its arsenals.

1433
02:11:43,855 --> 02:11:46,149
It's human nature, Charles.

1434
02:11:47,859 --> 02:11:49,194
I still have hope.

1435
02:11:50,487 --> 02:11:51,488
Oh, yes.

1436
02:11:52,906 --> 02:11:53,990
"Hope."

1437
02:11:54,825 --> 02:11:56,660
I was right about Raven.

1438
02:11:57,411 --> 02:11:59,079
I was even right about you.

1439
02:12:02,582 --> 02:12:04,084
What about the rest of the world?

1440
02:12:06,002 --> 02:12:08,713
Doesn't it ever wake you up
in the middle of the night?

1441
02:12:10,882 --> 02:12:13,927
The feeling that one day
they'll come for you...

1442
02:12:14,094 --> 02:12:16,179
and your children.

1443
02:12:17,597 --> 02:12:19,349
It does, indeed.

1444
02:12:19,516 --> 02:12:22,352
What do you do when you wake up to that?

1445
02:12:23,562 --> 02:12:26,022
I feel a great swell of pity
for the poor soul...

1446
02:12:26,189 --> 02:12:29,526
that comes to my school
looking for trouble.

1447
02:12:34,531 --> 02:12:36,741
You're sure I can't convince you to stay?

1448
02:12:38,410 --> 02:12:40,203
You're psychic, Charles.

1449
02:12:40,704 --> 02:12:42,581
You can convince me to do anything.

1450
02:12:45,375 --> 02:12:47,043
Goodbye, old friend.

1451
02:12:47,961 --> 02:12:49,546
Good luck, Professor.

1452
02:12:54,968 --> 02:12:56,448
Forget everything you think you know.

1453
02:12:58,388 --> 02:13:00,765
Whatever lessons you learned in school...

1454
02:13:02,142 --> 02:13:04,060
whatever your parents taught you.

1455
02:13:05,562 --> 02:13:08,398
None of that matters!

1456
02:13:09,900 --> 02:13:11,735
You're not kids anymore.

1457
02:13:12,319 --> 02:13:13,945
You're not students.

1458
02:13:18,074 --> 02:13:19,493
You're X-Men.

